snippet: All students who have applied for the NTU india connect internship program (summer) via Google form must report to the Board Room (Director office) at 12 noon tomorrow for an interview. Again only
subject: Re: NTU India Connect Summer Internship
body:
All students who have applied for the NTU india connect internship program
(summer) via Google form must report to the Board Room (Director office) at
12 noon tomorrow for an interview.

Again only students who have applied must come for the interview.

Please come with relevant documents

Thank you.

On Sat, Jan 21, 2023 at 9:45 PM Dean - International Relations VIT, Pune <
dean.ir@vit.edu> wrote:

> Dear Student,
>
>   If you are interested in NTU India Connect Summer Internship then please
> fill out this form
>
>
> https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc7aKMlI03ezHMYMw5ipLSEU2nkzRRNsoBVkq54_rfoSWYTwQ/viewform?usp=sf_link
>
>
>
>  Please see the details on the website
> https://www.ntu.edu.sg/about-us/global/india-connect-ntu/programme-details
>
> The summer internship period is 10 May 2023 – 23 July 2023   and
> application deadline to NTU Singapore  31st Jan 2023.
>
> Nomination letter from VIT is mandatory for this Internship.
>
> Eligibility: Student must have competed 5 semesters of UG study.
> *Please note that cost of study travel stay and food will be bourn by
> student only. Cost will be 4 to 6 Lakh Rs for the internship.*
>
> The process of applications is as follows
> 1. All interested students must fill out this Google form  by  23 th Jan
> 2023.
> 2. After that interviews will be held for interaction with the student.
> 3. Final list of nominated students will be made by 27th Jan.
> 4. The finalized students must apply on NTU Singapore website by 31Jan
> 2023 and submit all necessary documents.
>
>
>

[image: Google Forms]
I've invited you to fill out a form:
JP Morgan Internship + PPO 2024
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdJYM-hzXKN_BiQ7nQ3qm1kdnkva2dmi7WvBuTohaBp5lFxWw/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&flr=0&usp=mail_form_link>
Eligible Branches : B.Tech. CS, IT,E&TC ,Electronics,AIDS
Eligibility Criteria : with minimum aggregate 7 CGPA [until date] in
engineering course
Stipend : 50000/month
PPO : 15 lpa
Please note Internship will be in next semester.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Greetings from JP Morgan Chase & Co.!

As we embark on the campus hiring journey for the 2023 Software Engineer
Full-Time and Internship Programs, we would like to kick-start the process
with the Software Engineer Program Roadshow flagship event. We invite
students from your esteemed institute to participate in this event. The
event details are mentioned in the attached invite. Request you to share
the invite with the eligible students and encourage them to participate in
big numbers.
The student eligibility criteria, in order to apply for the Software
Engineer Program, are as follows:
Degrees: B.Tech./B.E./MCA
2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
Streams or Specializations: Computer Science/Information Science/
Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
A well-rounded academic background with minimum aggregate 7 CGPA [until
date] in engineering course
Fill out form
<https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdJYM-hzXKN_BiQ7nQ3qm1kdnkva2dmi7WvBuTohaBp5lFxWw/viewform?vc=0&c=0&w=1&flr=0&usp=mail_form_link>
Create your own Google Form
<https://docs.google.com/forms?usp=mail_form_link>

snippet: ELP gives you a chance to get technical experience at a very early stage of your education and develop skills by working on problems first-hand. Hello Studustry's ELP is a specially designed
subject:
Studustry's ELP (Experiential Learning Program) - Gain valuable
 experience & rewards by enrolling
body:
b"ELP gives you a chance to get technical experience at a very early stage of your education and develop skills by working on problems first-hand.

Hello 

Studustry's ELP is a specially designed program for you to get introduced to research and develop real world skills like problem solving, critical thinking, time management and much more.

As promised, we are sharing the link for all the ELP batches that are open for registration currently. Please click on the button below to take a look and enroll into one of them.

We promise, it will be an amazing experience for you and you will add a lot of valuable things to your skillset.

ELP Batches Available ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

In today's education landscape, it is very important to add real project experience to your resume along with the coursework that you complete in college.

It's a special program to introduce young talent to research and have them interact with other students and learn by solving real world problems.

You will be part of a cohort of 15-30 students each working on their own research. You will also get to interact with industry professionals, get feedback and rating and learn along with your peers.

Rewards -

* Receive feedback from industry professionals and showcase your work
* Receive a Certificate of participation and LoR
* Rewards\xa0up to Rs. 1500 to students who do well
* Weekly thought-provoking sessions online

Who should you participate?

* Students who wish to explore a new way of learning which is not governed by exams and assignments
* Students who are willing to give 5-6 hrs in a week to work on the project
* Students who wish to have purposeful interaction with peers and \xa0professionals

Please do let us if you have any more questions about this \xa0and I will do my best to get them resolved.
Don't wait! Sign-up now!

ELP Topics Available ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

Don't wait! Enroll ASAP as we have limited seats for each batch.

If you are already a part of a current ELP batch, use this email to show interest in participating in future ELP batches.

We are adding new batches every week, so keep visiting this link regularly to check out where you can participate next.

Upgrade yourself! ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

Use this link ( https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=919175188287 ) if you would like to ask questions about the project.
Studustry is a startup based in Pune & Aurangabad bringing the concept of project based learning to colleges in India. Look for our LinkedIn page to learn more about us.

( https://www.facebook.com/studustry/ ) ( https://twitter.com/studustry?lang=en ) ( https://www.instagram.com/studustry/?hl=en ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/studustry/ )

Venugopal

Paithan Road Itkheda , Aurangabad ,  431001

Unsubscribe ( http://url4692.studustry.com/asm/unsubscribe/?user_id=18854668&data=zNk3BdkgKTD-BDXw2BYFKO3NOn-2yF5IYRAeM_xND1cKQdA_qCAjB5EQ5Ynv27SAeCb3FK4lk0dPFRV2hxg0m9UermhLMdBDrkWZ3qk4-UpYheWQjfMCFz2th87huA_WoFe_LTwLMXww8Yjh_o1IyXbuJn8n4Ni3QTAsPDzSik_vEOeANflZddKHnJt2RhjmAr5clZds9ENEEmg2LIxvc0QeamPesnjFrDLXZKae8Yblsta1U13HFzg26-IYjzzN5DaN9MNvAYDQwagtE1O3uLEyK9aBVRWE6oEN0K3x1OvILvBSLVyOXwXu2lOP-NKtU1YWKxiw5-93PTWUX_P9p5ksFP6cqjVseIR0sHr9M8NfdGnjlP3l5jUKKE34t51cOiSd-rXhg-goabQgz614ISGlrlv6LAeUMDwZJ6aht1S3UkMX0sSQzN-0P1GbhYMhRgm3ZuvuM0boqynEAnubJYsFIj5RZmKJJHHkjTM9CKOi8EF_A0de-3zwMVsi1v2xpON2yMMn4wD61idGHSmGUsCzQGKbMoNfzNU1vC5nzrv3RARF6s1gSDA0Nn3xuu_bEXPu7qJwoP9i44ksdw05_GguAUxLvW05bv3ndyBTExnxxPAogIBCkrneR69cEJ10lX9alnfkSQJxQCqTZMz-lcMBTtQJQJtaiZjZ29621bTnwb6Ty9muCcoiMJpg5xkyQRuk1eos0B3xuIS6BeFnUYlqdmbB6AVuXmJppE8VudFfY4XFIIjrPjEazhrlvRDB5AoDvTsr5geRB39ZjOSOZLcGF7nTH0tjL7yUKmr9ZKMed2sRwT7846uY0C0pYMaqBVfXL7kHBb7u6tV7Z14pupMWP3sd0R_cjM6B5UAYSpDxdLFYo2a-Q-wL9MdxNsQBQApQuklWp5dHTi2deIiWXaXPKvOYnUMKWbUcl8Y9eC-Z0MFRa9w-VDuhSVH6q7JNT1yrDXZ55db6ZIQSjzOsJ4bdxiZ2EHlDiFDVD2c-2pBNrtSyUK3FQ4GxhrIX_tD0EXeVN6szeoGyIccgxkhGkU7FdmvSuTiaUQapv68wy2vHR1PbhgrkkaTtunc8XqZFd72YqeloduGtoMxiB2Gybg1t3D48Uj1TgJOEkgqOKDQz26eoNfvs0YMcgNes7tNXy0kdoYwjRyexd_SdkfPF8Q== )"

snippet: Greetings Everyone, CSI VIT Pune Student Branch is thrilled to announce its upcoming C++ workshop, which will begin on 18th January and teach you everything from scratch. Perks of C++ Workshop: Free
subject: Grab your Seats for C++ Workshop before it's too late!!
body:
Greetings Everyone,

CSI VIT Pune Student Branch is thrilled to announce its upcoming C++
workshop, which will begin on 18th January and teach you everything from
scratch.

Perks of C++ Workshop:

   - Free Certification
   - No prior Knowledge Required
   - Hands-on implementation and guidance
   - Good and Conceptual understanding of Object Oriented Programming


What You Will Learn

   - The Fundamentals of C++
   - Write fast and powerful C++ programs, compile the source code, and
   create executable files.
   - Learn Object-Oriented Programming Design Concept in C++ Perfectly with
   Examples
   - Learn best practices and avoid pitfalls via useful Do’s and Don’ts
   - Learn C++ features that allow you to program compact and
   high-performance C++ applications

Register Now ! <https://forms.gle/VNKKozgjR8gkL7br5>

>
>
> The registration process for the Code For Good 2022 is now open!
>
>
>
> *Please share the below registration details and the attached JD with your
> students and ask them to submit their formal application for the Software
> Engineer Program on our Careers page at the earliest. *
>
>
>
> *Please Note: The Code For Good event is the only way this year by which
> the students can apply for the Software Engineer Program (SEP) at JP Morgan
> Chase & Co. Hence, I request you to urge all eligible students to register
> themselves for the Code For Good 2022 at the earliest. *
>
>
>
> *Eligibility Criteria for registration for the Software Engineer Program:*
>
>    - *Degrees:* B.Tech./B.E./MCA
>    - 2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
>    - 2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
>    - *Streams or Specializations:* Computer Science/Information Science/
>    Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
>    Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
>    - A well-rounded academic background with *minimum aggregate 7 CGPA
>    [until date] in engineering course*
>
>
>
> *Registration Links:*
>
>    - The students from the 2023 graduating batch, who are applying for
>    the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, should click here
>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210245503/?utm_medium=jobshare>
>    to register themselves.
>    - The students from the 2024 graduating batch, who are applying for
>    the Internship opportunity in 2023, should click here
>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210247021/?utm_medium=jobshare>
>    to register themselves.
>
>
>
> *Registration Dates:*
>
>    - *The last day for registration for students from the 2024 graduating
>    batch, who are applying for the Internship opportunity in 2023, is 16th
>    March 2022. *
>    - *The last day for registration for students from the 2023 graduating
>    batch, who are applying for the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, is
>    16th March 2022. *
>
>
>
> *Selection Process:*
>
>    - Eligible students register themselves on the JP Morgan Chase Careers
>    page as per the given deadlines [as mentioned above].
>    - All eligible students appear for an online coding test. We will
>    share further details on the online tests at a later stage.
>    - All eligible students appear for a video interview
>    - JP Morgan Chase announces the final participant shortlist for the
>    Code For Good events
>
>
>
> *Important Points to Know:*
>
>    1. Click ‘Apply Now’ and sign in with your JPMC career site username
>    and associated personal email address. In case of you have previously
>    signed up with your college email address, please edit the email address to
>    your personal one before proceeding with this application. If you do not
>    recall your password click forgot your password and follow the instructions
>    2. Complete your application. If you are currently using an ‘.edu’
>    email address please update it to a personal non ‘.edu’ email address.
>    Failure to do so could cause delays in you receiving updates regarding your
>    candidacy. You will be required to attach your resume with a Photograph on
>    the right-hand/left-hand corner [Mandatory], kindly update your prior
>    internship experience with other skills [optional].
>    3. In case your campus does not appear in the application form, please
>    select ‘other’ and mention the campus in the free text field.
>    4. Click “Submit” to officially submit your application – a
>    confirmation will be sent to the email address on your account when your
>    application has been received
>
>
> <jaishree.bagul@jpmchase.com>
>
>
>
> Thanks & Regards
>

snippet: ELP gives you a chance to get technical experience at a very early stage of your education and develop skills by working on problems first-hand. Hello Studustry's ELP is a specially designed
subject:
Studustry's ELP (Experiential Learning Program) - Gain valuable
 experience & rewards by enrolling
body:
b"ELP gives you a chance to get technical experience at a very early stage of your education and develop skills by working on problems first-hand.

Hello 

Studustry's ELP is a specially designed program for you to get introduced to research and develop real world skills like problem solving, critical thinking, time management and much more.

As promised, we are sharing the link for all the ELP batches that are open for registration currently. Please click on the button below to take a look and enroll into one of them.

We promise, it will be an amazing experience for you and you will add a lot of valuable things to your skillset.

ELP Batches Available ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

In today's education landscape, it is very important to add real project experience to your resume along with the coursework that you complete in college.

It's a special program to introduce young talent to research and have them interact with other students and learn by solving real world problems.

You will be part of a cohort of 15-30 students each working on their own research. You will also get to interact with industry professionals, get feedback and rating and learn along with your peers.

Rewards -

* Receive feedback from industry professionals and showcase your work
* Receive a Certificate of participation and LoR
* Rewards\xa0up to Rs. 1500 to students who do well
* Weekly thought-provoking sessions online

Who should you participate?

* Students who wish to explore a new way of learning which is not governed by exams and assignments
* Students who are willing to give 5-6 hrs in a week to work on the project
* Students who wish to have purposeful interaction with peers and \xa0professionals

Please do let us if you have any more questions about this \xa0and I will do my best to get them resolved.
Don't wait! Sign-up now!

ELP Topics Available ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

Don't wait! Enroll ASAP as we have limited seats for each batch.

If you are already a part of a current ELP batch, use this email to show interest in participating in future ELP batches.

We are adding new batches every week, so keep visiting this link regularly to check out where you can participate next.

Upgrade yourself! ( https://airtable.com/shrWuL1P0HCnT3o6Q/tblzo4uC3e4oWP7zZ )

Use this link ( https://api.whatsapp.com/send?phone=919175188287 ) if you would like to ask questions about the project.
Studustry is a startup based in Pune & Aurangabad bringing the concept of project based learning to colleges in India. Look for our LinkedIn page to learn more about us.

( https://www.facebook.com/studustry/ ) ( https://twitter.com/studustry?lang=en ) ( https://www.instagram.com/studustry/?hl=en ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/studustry/ )

snippet: Dear Participant, Welcome aboard, we are happy to have you as one of the participants of IBM Hack Challenge 2022 powered by SmartInternz, in collaboration with IBM Global University Programs &
subject: Welcome to IBM Hack Challenge 2022!
body:
Dear Participant,

 Welcome aboard, we are happy to have you as one of the participants of IBM
Hack Challenge 2022 powered by SmartInternz, in collaboration with IBM
Global University Programs & AICTE.



 Here are the instructions to register and start your journey


 Step -1: Create IBM SkillsBuild and IBM Cloud Accounts

 You need to mandatorily create IBM SkillsBuild and IBM Cloud accounts by
using your institutional email ID (e.g. student@uit.in or students@uit.edu
etc.)

 Click Here for steps to create your IBM SkillsBuild and Cloud Accounts.

 If you don’t have an institutional email ID, Click Here to fill a form
and request for SmatInternz email ID, that you can then use to create IBM
SkillsBuild and Cloud Accounts.




 Step-2: Complete the Courses and Upload Your Skill Badges.
 You need to mandatorily complete the courses mentioned in the ‘Courses’
section and upload the skill badge verifiable link in the git repo provided
in the project workspace.


 Step-3: Attend the Technical Bootcamp.
 Attend the bootcamp to gain hands-on experience with Red Hat OpenShift, IBM
Cloud, AI Services, IBM Watson Studio, Cognos Analytics, AutoAI. Utilize
this learning in developing your solutions.


 Step-4: Enroll & Submit your Proposed Solution for Approval
 Register for any problem statement as a team or as an individual (min team
size 1, max 4). Submit your proposed solution in a pre-defined format for
approval.
 Once your solution is approved, you would need to assign the work among
your teammates (if you’re working in a team) /to yourself (if you’re
working individually). Mentor support will be provided when you are stuck.
Get started and develop your solution.
 Note: Ensure that your team members are all individually registered for the
event.



 Click Here to join our Telegram group, to get in touch with us for any
queries you encounter while completing the steps.




 Regards, Team SmartInternz SmartInternz

subject:
To fill Project Topics/Titles of projects (EDI/DAI/Major) and brief
 of project.
body:
Dear Students,

I request you to fill the *Area of Interest*, *project Topics/Titles of
projects (EDI/DAI/Major) and brief of project in 3-4 lines* in the shared
excel sheet *(Classes are mentioned tab wise. Select appropriate tab as per
your class).*



*Note:*

·       One Member (Group Leader) of the group should the data.

·       Classes are mentioned tab wise. Select appropriate tab as per your
class

·       Don’t delete/modify any Entry from the shared sheet.

·       Verify your PRN number, Roll number and name*(If PRN not mentioned
then add it) *


*Shared sheet Link:*

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/10Jnc9GCOLkegpLeCri7x2ckX61reUrMSabFd2Uwlktw/edit?usp=sharing



*Guidelines for selecting project Topic:*

*1.    **The title should have an innovative idea.*

*2.    **It should have a social impact. *

*3.    **You should be able to publish your work in a conference or
journal. *

*4.    **Use a collaborative development platform like github to host your
project. *



*Fill the details in a shared sheet till 27/08/2022 (Saturday), 02.00 pm.
Please consider this mail important and fill data on priority basis.*

*For Any Queries, feel free to contact me.*


Thanks and regards,
*Amruta. A. Mankawade*
*Assistant Professor,*
*Department of IT and Artificial Intelligence-Data Science.*
*VIT, Pune.*

body:
* We are recruiting Heads and Secretaries' 22-23! *

*“The strength of the team is it's each individual member. The strength of
each member is the team.”*



*Greetings!✨ *



We at CSI, VIT Pune firmly believe in the way a team plays as a whole
determines its success. One may have the greatest bunch of individual stars
in the world, but if they don’t play together, the club won’t be worth a
dime. It’s the ability to work together towards a common vision and to
direct individual actions in a collaborative manner to achieve team goals.
The committee has extensively contributed in enlightening the masses about
crucial concepts required in the field of Information Technology.

subject:
Fwd: Student Innovation festival under aegis of India International
 Science festival (IISF) Bhopal 22-25 January, 2023-regarding
body:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: registrar vit <registrar@vit.edu>
Date: Thu, Dec 29, 2022 at 3:45 PM
Subject: Fwd: Student Innovation festival under aegis of India
International Science festival (IISF) Bhopal 22-25 January, 2023-regarding
To: <teachingstaff@vit.edu>




---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: All India Council for Technical Education(no-reply) <
admin@aicte-india.org>
Date: Thu, 29 Dec 2022, 15:25
Subject: Student Innovation festival under aegis of India International
Science festival (IISF) Bhopal 22-25 January, 2023-regarding



Dear Madam/Sir,
Greetings from All India Council for Technical Education!

India International Science Festival (IISF) is a platform for
public participation to inculcate scientific perspective and promote
interest in science. Seven editions of IISF have been organized at various
places across the country in the past. This year, the 8th* edition* of
*IISF* is being organized at *Maulana Azad National Institute of Technology
(MANIT), Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh*. Theme for the 8th edition of IISF is
Marching Towards Amrit Kaal with Science, Technology and Innovation.

In IISF-2022, *Students Innovation Festival (SIF)* is an event where
college level onwards students participate in competition and also showcase
their talents on an international stage. The Themes of SIF-2022 are:
Developing Sustainable Life based on Five Elements of Nature: The
Earth (पृथ्वी), The water (जल),The fire (तेजस /अग्नि), The air (हवा) and
The space (आकाश). Students from engineering as well as science streams, who
are interested and involved in innovation and creativity can participate in
the Students’ Innovation Festival (SIF-2022).

The selected models/entries will be showcased in the IISF on *22-23 January
2023* at MANIT, Bhopal. Registration can be done on the website-
https://scienceindiafest.org
<https://ind01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fscienceindiafest.org%2F&data=05%7C01%7CLokender.singh%40lntinfotech.com%7C75495b7afaa847a051ca08dae9797410%7C02aa9fc118bc4798a020e01c854dd434%7C1%7C0%7C638079005206305476%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=tip0Qn8bqGRCAPy6SA2F5uzzTENQTrPk2ReHLt86Ugw%3D&reserved=0>
. For detailed information, Brochure and Poster of SIF-2022 are enclosed
herewith. The last date for registration by the students is *10th January
2023*.

In view of the above, AICTE requests your Institution(s) to promote
participation of the students in SIF 2022 and also disseminate this
information among all the faculty members, Students, staff & others.

PFA:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/15zYcqh55Rn1ik6Lqu6Vip4_Ui06fBdcK/view?usp=share_lin

snippet: Dear author, We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION
subject: REMINDER FOR REGISTRATION - AOTA 2023
body:
Dear author,


We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.

 
A special registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.

 
You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author / presenting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6

 
Extended registration deadline: 5th January, 2023.

 
With best regards

 
TEAM AOTA

NOTE: YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

body:
Dear All,
                  Please note that students of classes  TY-IT,
TYAI&DS-A and TY AI&DS-B need to follow the same groups of last semester
ie.Sem-I of Academic year 2022-23 for this semester also. No one is allowed
to change their groups.

Note: Reporting to your respective guide will be monitored throughout the
semester. Non-performing students within the group will be monitored by the
guide and also group members need to report to the guide about them.
Performance will be evaluated on this parameter too.

Reminder: Everyone needs to enter the title and area of their EDI topics in
the sheet shared till 05 Jan 2022. Consider it on priority basis.

snippet: NVIDIA Software Engineer 6M Intern Hiring Test - 20 Jan 2023 Powered by HackerRank Hey There! Hope you are doing well and keeping safe. You have come a long way and we are very pleased to send you the
subject:
Test Invites - NVIDIA System Software Engineer Hiring Test - 3rd
 December 2022
body:
NVIDIA Software Engineer 6M Intern Hiring Test - 20 Jan 2023 - powered by HackerRank



  
    
      
        
        
          

 

Hey There!

Hope you are doing well and keeping safe. 

You have come a long way and we are very pleased to send you the invite for NVIDIA System Software Intern Hiring - 20th January 2023. As part of the assessment process, there would be a test followed by interviews for shortlisted candidates.

The technical screening test will be held on Friday, 20th January 2023  

Please note that the test log-in is valid for 30 minutes starting 5:00 PM

To ensure that you do not lose time while logging in to start the test, we recommend you fill the registration required for the test before the test login i.e. 5:30 PM. While registering, please ensure to keep the resume handy for uploading.

We have some information about the test which we think might be useful:


	This is a 60-minute test 
	The test would focus on Analytical/Problem solving, Programming/Coding, Data Structures and OS


 

Wish You all the best!!

 NVIDIA University Relations

        
        
      
      
        
          Duration: 60 min
          
          
          Start Login Date/Time:
          
            20 Jan 2023 07:00 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
          
          End Login Date/Time: 20 Jan 2023 07:30 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
            Start Test
          
          You can also use
          this link
          to access the test
          
          anytime before the test expiry date above.
          Please check date and time in your time zone.
          
          
        
      
    
  


Please note once you begin the test the timer will start and the test cannot be paused. Hence it is highly recommended that you complete the test in one sitting.

In case of power failure or loss of internet connection, the test timer will continue to run even though you might not be attempting it, in such a case please contact us by replying back to this email.

For any technical queries, please refer to https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Fsections%2F115001822568-FAQs/boIq6TYN/EDcI/qZevMXKcPK/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl or contact us at https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Frequests%2Fnew%3Fticket_form_id%3D360001035834./b4Iq6TYN/EDcI/LKbF22maLV/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl

HackerRank only provides a platform to conduct the tests. It does not schedule or evaluate any hiring tests or conduct interviews for any company. Hence for any of the above requests please contact the company that sent you the invite.

snippet: Dear All, EDI/DAI End Sem Exam Review is scheduled on 21 and 22 December 2022 , 10.0 am onwards. Detailed schedule for the same is attached in the excel file below. Following are the deliverables to
subject: End Sem Exam of EDI/DAI(Offline mode)
body:
*Dear All,*



 *EDI/DAI  End Sem Exam Review is scheduled on 21 and 22 December 2022 ,
10.0 am onwards. Detailed schedule for the same is attached in the excel
file below.*



 *Following are the deliverables to your Project Guide. Please see that you
submit everything in a folder to your Guide on or before 16 Dec 2022 .*


o  *     Complete project with code and necessary library in folder (name
folder with your class_ groupID)*

o  *     Power Point Presentation*

o  *     Screenshots of Output*

o  *     IEEE format research paper in Doc/Docx. format only*

o  *     Plagiarism Report of research paper.*

·             *Black book -for Final Year students*

·             *Publication Status and Certificate proof.*

o  *     Proof of any award or prize won if any (Related to Project) *

*Instructions:*



·       *The students will be evaluated by their respective Guide along
with an External Examiner *.*All the groups under the guidance of
respective Guide need to report at provided location and time as per
timetable.*



·       *The review will be conducted offline in respective Labs. *



·       Time for presentation is 10-15 Min and 5 min of Question Answer.



*  Format for Mid Semester Assessment*

End-Semester Assessment  will be of 100 Marks to be converted to 70 Marks.

[image: image.png]

Thanks and regards
*Amruta. A. Mankawade*
*Assistant Professor,*
*Department of IT and Artificial Intelligence-Data Science.*
*VIT, Pune.*

snippet: Dear author, We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY
subject:
FINAL REMINDER3 - Invitation for registration and presentation in AOTA -
  2023
body:
Dear author,


We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 12th January, 2022.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION AND COMMENTS IF APPLICABLE WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

subject: Result is declared  (B.Tech First year, AY 2020-21 Sem-I )
body:
Dear Student,


Result of B.Tech First year, AY 2020-21 Sem-I is declared today on 17th May
2021.


*Result of B.Tech FY  is visible in student's VIERP  login using following
steps*

1. Login to www.vierp.in

2. Click on 'Examinations->Result'

3. click on results 2020-21 sem-I.


If *FNP* status is visible on the marksheet then contact the accounts
section on *accounts@vit.edu <accounts@vit.edu>*. If *RR *status is visible
on the marksheet then contact the student section *vishal.kakade@vit.edu
<vishal.kakde@vit.edu>.*


If a student is not able to see the result in VIERP login  they can contact
the exam section by writing a mail to exam@vit.edu.




*DO NOT REPLY TO THIS MAIL.*

snippet: Dear JP Morgan Registered, Please go through below mail received from the company : ------------------------- Greetings from JP Morgan Chase & Co.! Online Test Date & Time : 18th March 2022 (
subject:
Re: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Hacker rank test details for
 2022-23 and 2023-24 batch
body:
Dear J P Morgan Registered,

Please  go through below mail received from the company :
-------------------------

Greetings from JP Morgan Chase & Co.!



   - *Online Test Date & Time : 18th March 2022 (Friday) at 8.00 AM IST for
   both Full-time and Internship hiring process*
   - *Test link will be received directly on the registered mail id of the
   candidate*



Please find below *important instructions for the** online coding test* with
respect to the Software Engineer Program [SEP] selection process. Please
share the same with all eligible and interested students* :*



   - The online coding test is the first step in the SEP selection process
   - We will use the *HackerRank* platform to conduct the test
   - *Students can start the test between 18th March 2022 8 AM IST till
   21st March 2022 8 AM IST.* Students will not be able to access the test
   outside of this time window.
   - This is a programming test of 100 marks having 2 programming
questions carrying
   50 marks each.
   - There is no negative marking; the students should try to attempt all
   questions
   - The time allowed for this test is 60 Minutes. The students can revisit
   the questions any number of times
   - *Switching between tabs,* *while attempting the test,* *is considered
   a violation and is, hence, not allowed*
   - *The test is proctored.* Copying from others or trying to look for
   solutions over the web is prohibited and will lead to rejection of
   candidature
   - *The students will be allowed to start the test only after they have
   switched on their webcam*
   - Before starting the test, the students have been asked to mention a
   few personal details [Name, email ID etc.]. *They should enter the same
   details that they have used to apply for the Software Engineer Program on
   the JP Morgan Chase & Co. Careers page.*
   - For queries related to HackerRank test or the platform please mail -
   hackerrank.support.cases@jpmchase.com


-------------------------
All the best!
Thanks.
A.S. Mitragotri
TPO,
VIT

>
> *Only the eligible students who register for the Code for Good via the
> link will receive the assessment email*
>
>
>
> Request you to kindly push for the registrations.
>
>
>
> Regards,
>
> Jaishree
>
>
>
> --------------------------------
>
>  Dear All,
>
>
>
> The registration process for the Code For Good 2022 is now open!
>
>
>
> Please share the below registration details and the attached JD with your
> students and ask them to submit their formal application for the Software
> Engineer Program on our Careers page at the earliest*.*
>
>
>
> *Please Note: The Code For Good event is the only way this year by which
> the students can apply for the Software Engineer Program (SEP) at JP Morgan
> Chase & Co. Hence, I request you to urge all eligible students to register
> themselves for the Code For Good 2022 at the earliest.*
>
>
>
> *Eligibility Criteria for registration for the Software Engineer Program:*
>
>    - *Degrees:* B.Tech./B.E./MCA
>    - 2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
>    - 2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
>    - *Streams or Specializations:* Computer Science/Information Science/
>    Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
>    Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
>    - A well-rounded academic background with *minimum aggregate 7 CGPA
>    [until date] in engineering course*
>
>
>
> *Registration Links:*
>
>    - The students from the 2023 graduating batch, who are applying for
>    the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, should click here
>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210245503/?utm_medium=jobshare> to
>    register themselves.
>    - The students from the 2024 graduating batch, who are applying for
>    the Internship opportunity in 2023, should click here
>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210247021/?utm_medium=jobshare> to
>    register themselves.
>
>
>
> *Registration Dates:*
>
>    - The last day for registration for students from the 2024 graduating
>    batch, who are applying for the Internship opportunity in 2023, is 16th March
>    2022.
>    - The last day for registration for students from the 2023 graduating
>    batch, who are applying for the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, is 16
>    th March 2022.
>
>
>
> *Selection Process:*
>
>    - Eligible students register themselves on the JP Morgan Chase Careers
>    page as per the given deadlines [as mentioned above].
>    - All eligible students appear for an online coding test. We will
>    share further details on the online tests at a later stage.
>    - All eligible students appear for a video interview
>    - JP Morgan Chase announces the final participant shortlist for the
>    Code For Good events
>
>
>
> *Important Points to Know:*
>
>    1. Click ‘Apply Now’ and sign in with your JPMC career site username
>    and associated personal email address. In case of you have previously
>    signed up with your college email address, please edit the email address to
>    your personal one before proceeding with this application. If you do not
>    recall your password click forgot your password and follow the instructions
>    2. Complete your application. If you are currently using an ‘.edu’
>    email address please update it to a personal non ‘.edu’ email address.
>    Failure to do so could cause delays in you receiving updates regarding your
>    candidacy. You will be required to attach your resume with a Photograph on
>    the right-hand/left-hand corner [Mandatory], kindly update your prior
>    internship experience with other skills [optional].
>    3. In case your campus does not appear in the application form, please
>    select ‘other’ and mention the campus in the free text field.
>    4. Click “Submit” to officially submit your application – a
>    confirmation will be sent to the email address on your account when your
>    application has been received
>
>
>

snippet: Dear author, We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY
subject: Final reminder 2 - Invitation for presentation registration in AOTA - 2023
body:
Dear author,

We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 10th January, 2023.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION AND COMMENTS IF APPLICABLE WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

snippet: Hi Om, Here's your chance to join Synopsys as a Technical Engineering Intern! Stipend: INR 35000/month (via glassdoor) Application Link: https://unstop.com/internship/technical-engineering-
subject: Synopsys is hiring Technical Engineering Interns @ INR 35,000/month!
body:
Hi Om,

Here's your chance to join Synopsys as a Technical Engineering Intern!

Stipend: INR 35,000/month (via glassdoor)

Application Link: https://unstop.com/internship/technical-engineering-internship-synopsys-585403

You should have strong fundamentals in Digital electronics, and assist with one or more of the following activities based on the project assigned: Verilog/System Verilog/ Vera coding, Exposure to UVM methodology, working with EDA tools like Design Compiler for Synthesis, SpyGlass for Lint, VCS for simulation, architecture exploration of the sub-blocks within one of these IPs to optimize for the area, speed, and power.

Apply now to join one of the Fortune 500 companies!

For more details, click here.

Regards,
Team Unstop

subject:
L&T Technology Services | TECHgium 6th Edition | Global Innovation
 Challenge | Invitation to Register
body:
---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: VI Central T&P <tpo@vit.edu>
Date: Tue, Aug 30, 2022 at 12:09 PM
Subject: Fwd: L&T Technology Services | TECHgium 6th Edition | Global
Innovation Challenge | Invitation to Register
To: TPO - Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Pune <tpo_students@vit.edu>



 Thanks and Regards,

[image: VIT]

*Karthick S B*
Professor, Department of  Computer Engineering
Dean Industry Relations,
Vishwakarma Institute of Technology
Central Training and Placement Officer
Vishwakarma Institutes, Pune
Mobile: 7385231260 Alternate No.:
Website: www.vit.edu
<https://www.linkedin.com/school/vishwakarma-institute-of-technology-pune/>
<https://twitter.com/vitpune>
<https://www.facebook.com/Vishwakarma-Institute-Of-Technology-1547575875489422/>



---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Campus Connect <Campus.Connect@ltts.com>
Date: Tue, Aug 30, 2022 at 11:58 AM
Subject: L&T Technology Services | TECHgium 6th Edition | Global Innovation
Challenge | Invitation to Register
To:






Dear Sir/Madam,



*We are proud to announce and invite you to be a part of our sixth edition
of TECHgium® - 2022 !*



TECHgium® is a multi-stage Innovation competition by L&T Technology
Services for students across the world.



*TECHgium® provides a platform for *

   - Students to engage on real-world industry use cases and challenges to
   come up with solutions and taking a step towards industry readiness
   - For institutes and faculty to engage with industry challenge
   statements along with the students and thereby taking steps towards
   bridging gap between industry and academia
   - Top 3 winning teams take away prizes worth 18 Lakhs.



Please find attached TECHgium poster and brochure that has details and
timeline that you may use to circulate to the students.



The below is the process for TECHgium registration and participation.



   1. *Stage1: *

*Step1: Institute registration *

                                                               i.
Institute
register on TECHgium portal (https://ltts.techgium.com
<https://ind01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fltts.techgium.com%2F&data=05%7C01%7CVijay.Mantri%40Ltts.com%7C1ff587a5a5794b9df83d08da84f9317f%7C311b33788e8a4b5ea33fe80a3d8ba60a%7C0%7C0%7C637968503087222071%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=axMQDWHPikZe1bMA3sO3HwD3cUom%2FfnBllo6bVvM11E%3D&reserved=0>).
This process generates a unique institute id. (Institute can sign in, if
already registered earlier)

                                                             ii.      The
unique institute id is passed on to the students by the institute along
with the poster and brochures of the event received through LTTS.

*Step2: Student registration*

                                                           iii.      Students
(pre-final and final year of their engineering degree) register on the
portal and use the unique institute id to complete their respective
registration

*Step3:  Challenge Statement selection by students and concept submission*

                                                           iv.      Students
view the challenge statements available on TECHgium portal. Any queries can
also be submitted through the portal.

                                                             v.      Students
submit concept note against selected challenge statement on the portal.

                                                           vi.      Students
have the option to invite faculty from their institutes as mentor who can
guide them through this journey.

Shortlisted students move to Stage2



   1. *Stage2: *

*Step4: Full Technical Paper*

                                                               i.      Students
work on technical paper/presentation around the concept suggested by them
in stage1.

                                                             ii.
Shortlisted
students are invited for presentation to a Jury identified by LTTS

Shortlisted students move to Stage3.



   1. *Stage3:*

*Step5: Proof Of Concept (POC) Demonstration *

                                                               i.      Students
work on a POC of their solution.

                                                             ii.      Students
showcase their POC to Jury identified by LTTS.

                                                           iii.      Students
demonstrating POCs have option to appear for LTTS recruitment process

Shortlisted students move to Stage 4 finale presentation.



   1. *Stage4:*

*Step6: Finale Presentation*

                                                               i.
Presentation
by students to LTTS identified Jury.



   1. *Stage5:*

*Step7: Award Ceremony*

                                                               i.      Top
3 Winner announcement.



*Top 3 Prizes*

*1st Prize ~ 10 Lakhs*

*2nd Prize ~ 5 Lakhs*

*3rd Prize ~ 3 Lakhs*



*Apart from the awards and prizes for the winners, all the participants of
POC demonstration round of this competition will be called for
Pre-Placement process at LTTS.*



Please feel free to write to us at TECHgium@ltts.com in case of any queries
in this regard.



We look forward to an enthusiastic participation in TECHgium® 6th Edition

subject: Regarding the interview process !!
body:
Greetings fellow developer,

As you may know, we have successfully come to an end of the interview
process for the 2021-'22 tenure for our club. It has been a tough decision
on our part as all the candidates were exceptionally good and talented. But
there are only so many positions we could fill. So we regret to inform you
that we could not proceed with your application.☹

Don't be disheartened, we still equally value your presence and would love
to see you participate actively in our workshops and events. And try again
next year.

We wish you all the very best for the future.☺

-- 
Regards
DSC Team
Vishwakarma Institute of Technology,
Bibwewadi, Pune, Maharashtra, India

snippet: Dear Om Surushe, Your paper "Software Runtimes for Disaggregated Memory: A Review Paper" has been included in the proceedings of SPICON-2022 to be published by IEEE. IEEE requires that an
subject: IEEE copyright agreement for your SPICON-2022 paper
body:
Dear Om Surushe,

Your paper "Software Runtimes for Disaggregated Memory: A Review Paper" has been included in the proceedings of
SPICON-2022 to be published by IEEE. IEEE requires that an author of
every published paper signs a copyright agreement.

EasyChair is a vendor authorized by IEEE to handle copyright
agreements. To sign the agreement via EasyChair, you should

  (1) log in to EasyChair;

  (2) click on "Alerts" in the main menu;

  (3) click on "IEEE copyright agreement for paper Software Runtimes for Disaggregated Memory: A Review Paper"

If there is no such link under your Alerts menu tab, then one of the
authors already signed the agreement on behalf of all authors.

__________________________________________________
Please be aware that this is an unmonitored email alias,
so please do not reply to this email.
To contact EasyChair use the EasyChair contact Web page
https://easychair.org/contact

snippet: Dear students, You are hereby instructed to check the fees receipts for the fees paid in your learner.vierp.in login. If you have paid the fees through RTGS/NEFT and not entered the transaction details
subject: Regarding fees payment and fees receipts.
body:
Dear students,

You are hereby instructed to check the fees receipts for the fees paid in
your learner.vierp.in login.

If you have paid the fees through RTGS/NEFT and not entered the transaction
details from your vierp login, Please fill the RTGS/NEFT details from your
lerarner.vierp.in login for generation of fees receipt.

Follow the steps after fees payment by RTGS/NEFT/IMPS
1) Login to https://learner.vierp.in
2) Go to Accounts -> pay fees -> click on NEFT
3) Bank details are available to make payment by NEFT/RTGS.
4) After making payment through NEFT/RTGS, fill up the details of payments
in your login -> Accounts -> pay fees -> click on NEFT.
5) Upload the transaction proof and save.

After entering the NEFT details in vierp, receipt of the same will be
generated in your login within two working days after verification from our
bank.

If you do not find any receipt for the fees paid or find any discrepancies
in the fees receipt mail to accounts.fees@vit.edu alongwith the attachment
of fees payment proof.

Please ignore if your proper receipt is generated in your login.


-- 
Mrunal Barve
Accounts Officer
*VISHWAKARMA INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY*,
Pune - 37, (Maharashtra) India.
*www.vit.edu <http://www.vit.edu/>*
Ph - 020 - 24202251

snippet: Our team, Endurance Racing is synonymous to unparalleled off-roading events for thrill seekers. We represent VIT at BAJA SAE INDIA and several other prestigious events worldwide. We at endurance, are
subject: Recruitment for the official BAJA team of VIT- Endurance Racing.
body:
Our team, *Endurance Racing* is synonymous to unparalleled off-roading
events for thrill seekers. We represent VIT at *BAJA SAE INDIA* and several
other prestigious events worldwide. We at endurance, are true car
enthusiasts and put together a sturdy ATV that leaves a distinct mark with
its very presence, at the competition.

To achieve this, we need to think out of the box, equipped with the
21st century
skills and most importantly a hell-bent team to do so. Our team is in
pursuit of learners who have the zeal and would like to showcase their
hands-on techniques and core values in building our next ATV, *HAWK X2.*

With an experience of more than a decade now, we welcome learners to seize
this opportunity- if you believe that you are proactive enough to make your
place in our team.

<https://forms.gle/c4Ee7KFnuCDrDKp57>

Recruitment details are as follows:

Stage 1: Technical Interview

(Basic physics and automotive knowledge will be tested.)

Date: 23rd May, Sunday.



Further stages and dates to be disclosed later.

*Know what fuels you by registering in the google form given below:*

https://forms.gle/c4Ee7KFnuCDrDKp57

Stay Tuned to know more on:

Instagram- https://www.instagram.com/team_endurance_racing/?hl=en

Pratik Badhe: 7738630175

Mangesh Shinde: 9307500469



*Be a part of nothing less than, THE BEST. *

snippet: Dear Studsnts Hands-On Web Development Certification Training followed by a Guaranteed Internship for students of Vishwakarma Institute Of Technology, Pune. Please note that TOMORROW, ie 24th of
subject:
Vishwakarma Institute Of Technology, Pune has been shortlisted for
 Bolt's Scholarship on Web Development
body:
Dear Studsnts



Hands-On Web Development Certification Training followed by a Guaranteed
Internship for students of Vishwakarma Institute Of Technology, Pune.
Please note that TOMORROW, i.e. 24th of January 2023 is the LAST DAY for
students to avail this offer.





Critical: Students from 1st year to final year are eligible for this
opportunity. Please do share this opportunity with all the students.







Scholarship for Students of Vishwakarma Institute Of Technology, Pune:

   - Students have to answer the scholarship test using this link:
*https://info.boltiot.com/webdevelopmentscholarship
   <https://czvL704.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/T8+113/czvL704/VVSNDf3_1fdPW8cc2Dn6Xfw7cW3mxgk34W6BDpN1vWRt73q90_V1-WJV7CgDz-W594S4k6rLZ7RW96ncs38sxXtBW1gnnDj2S5_ZYW78XYlN3Zwk-fW2dWKHD6w8MyvW7nR953331xX3W3MjDKV1lTlX3W6TyNW64bFbPdN9jYvFRh021KW6QdJ-521Z4t9W2FLS0Q8WXD9zW6MJ7FV4n716cW39fNs98ZrpLGW1G5ScK7Y7qDCW5nyYzV5hXPt9W956DkT5NDLvnW7Q0H8y406RMlN99MwTvv23q2V2N1Fj4WYWV6W60r4Kc6bF-DpW8wlPQ_1T3ZcXW1kcNZp5MnGx2W4lhp2q2mkMdCW42lV926vk6qSW55Jt371Q45rpW7G90TF5306MQW9kykRj8yb0Z5W3wV8lc7XRvyRW1d7K3D4672TrW4mR9S97TzZFh3gx71>*

   - Upon qualifying for the scholarship test,  students can *avail of the
   training at* 90% OFF.

   - The students only have to pay Rs. 990/- towards the training if they
   qualify for the test. The original price of the training is Rs. 8,600/-.

   - The training will also be *followed by a guaranteed internship*.






What's in it for the students?

   - Students can *practically implement what they learn via this hands-on
   training*. In addition, our mentors will be available if they need any
   assistance during the training or while building the projects.

   - Students have *lifetime access* to the training, they can *learn
   anytime* and at their own pace.

   - *Certificate of completion *of the training as well as the internship.

   - *Guaranteed Internship* upon training completion with a certificate
   that can be submitted to the college.

   - We cover *programming languages* and technologies like 'HTML, CSS,
   JavaScript, React, and AJAX' *from basics*. Students *need not have any
   prior knowledge*.



   - *The option of a full refund* in case the students are not happy with
   the training offered to them.

   - Link for students of Vishwakarma Institute Of Technology, Pune :
*https://info.boltiot.com/webdevelopmentscholarship
   <https://czvL704.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/T8+113/czvL704/VVSNDf3_1fdPW8cc2Dn6Xfw7cW3mxgk34W6BDpN1vWRt73q90_V1-WJV7CgR7NW2j_D4J7vDjbHW2mm8RC1rb0qWW1y2Jzp3rbvWPW2RVq0K51_g70W2D1hls4VXLYhW1P6r_-1FyYkNW6csSVL9kyjX3W443CsM7b0ZtkW4H5YlM30ByLlW1Sqm515TjdCzW6z70X84zgPv4W10wzKM8MDnJtW5Yq2nZ8w3TgjW86q97F7JJP3qN7BkfXtk5z02W1twfkp3NhDzDW46Qrs42r-P5zN8hzwsYjgMQnW3YVTXm6H_RfZW1WSNmC50Yw-sVpmzhJ8H-VkSW4QlKJR5dyk27W80XMXZ7kcYfTW5z2Ml-8crLwnW7ZtqmG1RjpkvV4VfLn3w_pGLW6SJxr26M9XrLW484M3Y6VtLW1W1TJ87x58xGWnN8z5Tl8wxS6G3lMQ1>*





Next steps for faculty:

   - The *last date to avail of the scholarship is TOMORROW, the 24th of
   January 2023.*


   - Please share about this program with your students by forwarding this
   email to them at the earliest.

   - You may also share via WhatsApp message by clicking here:
   https://info.boltiot.com/whatsappshareforwebdevelopment
   <https://czvL704.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/T8+113/czvL704/VVSNDf3_1fdPW8cc2Dn6Xfw7cW3mxgk34W6BDpN1vWRt73q90_V1-WJV7CgZV7W8tgM926TGY1ZW2WXSrq1TMm4WN1_H1ZTNKvGCN5DbL6wd-n-1N3ttR_X4bH3DW9jt8yN3yqD1fW6PJ8_940dfxLW7XmgG73HK9SBW6ppRMc3Bz1fpW2wcK0Y34p3dRW8-qyyP3pm8GdW3P3YHb5YrwJHN4PpHCvDyS5fW5vd0bw2TH69pVJlPrC4nHN4ZW1_2fQn8THZN1W5bD3_v7rQRTnW16Kp4L1JLKd9W6_nG3Z6Gh1pwW8z6dkV3gYt-LW1cBvQX59-qC-W230YV22hVLddW3G13dY91btz3W7l56LM3Gb-LqW3l23QB8d_32wW5pMk2C3k6KVDW91Nk2g3DFk3zW34t70w42Y1q6W8zDHzT3Z_NmKW7J-Sdl4rXL3c2Zj1>

snippet: F.No. AICTE/P&AP/Misc/Jan/2023 Date: 09.01.2023 Circular To, All Vice Chancellors of Technical Universities and All Directors/Principals of AICTE Approved Institutions. India International Science
subject:
=?UTF-8?Q?Request_to_participate_in_Student_Innovation_Festiva?=
	=?UTF-8?Q?l_=E2=80=93_IISF_2022?=
body:
*F.No. AICTE/P&AP/Misc/Jan/2023


                  Date: 09.01.2023*
*Circular*

* To,*


*All Vice Chancellors of Technical Universities and**        All
Directors/Principals of AICTE Approved Institutions.*

            *India International Science Festival (IISF) *is a platform for
public participation to inculcate scientific perspective and promote
interest in science. Seven editions of IISF have been organized at various
places across the country in the past. This year, eighth edition of IISF is
being organized at *Maulana Azad Naitonal Institute of Technology (MANIT),
Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh.* Theme for the 8th edition of IISF is Marching
Towards Amrit Kaal with Science, Technology and Innovation.

             *Students Innovation Festival (SIF)* is an event of IISF where
college level onwards students participate in competition and also showcase
their talents on an international stage. The Themes of SIF-2022 are:
*Developing
Sustainable Life based on Five Elements of Nature: The Earth, The Water,
The fire, The air and The space*. Students from engineering as well as
science streams, who are interested and involved in innovation and
creativity can participate in the *Students’ Innovation Festival
(SIF-2022).*

            The selected models/entries will be showcased in the IISF on *22-23
January, 2023 at MANIT, Bhopal*. Registration can be done on the website
https://scienceindiafest.org
<https://ind01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fscienceindiafest.org%2F&data=05%7C01%7CSubhash.Kumar%40lntinfotech.com%7Cdcc716fce2c24c4a93fd08daf23fd8d7%7C02aa9fc118bc4798a020e01c854dd434%7C1%7C0%7C638088653485414394%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=rRM%2FNkIuZQR7VkXtLUqf67YnjGxHH6UB5Xt%2FQEQgQro%3D&reserved=0>
.
For detailed information, *Brochure and Poster of SIF-2022 are enclosed
herewith*. The last date for registration by the students is *13th January,
2023.*

            In this regard you are requested to encourage students at your
institutions to be part of such endeavour towards innovation. Your
cooperation will help the students of every corner of our country to have
opportunity to participate in such an event of National importance.

PFA:-
https://drive.google.com/file/d/130Ou99W9nwpPgauG-iX5B_3rWZ5shrtb/view?usp=share_link


PFA:-
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1i7_aoKukYzS9LjbT8W-mtGD7AYJ454qm/view?usp=share_link





*Regards,**(Dr. Ramesh Unnikrishnan)*


*                                      Advisor-II**Policy & Academic
Planning Bureau*

-- 
*Prof. Dr. Mane Vijay M.*
Dean Analytics
Associate  Professor - Department of E& TC Engineering,
*Technical Competition Coordinator,*
*Mobile No - 9822550134*
*Email Id : vijay.mane@vit.edu <vijay.mane@vit.edu>*
*Room No - 1221*
*Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Pune - 37.*
Bibwewadi, Pune,
Maharashtra, India.

subject: You can now choose your YouTube handle
body:
YouTube is introducing handles to make it easier for people to find and  
connect with each other.  
<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ACnX6LZN4o8ga1Y0Z6NLUDnikW7tvHkCYXE27WDxblC-Ukj0qkR8HmSAqtEPNdZjfHT_Aj8kn6qDA4ngtXsX0ZEMo7uJdzxypGNUhKoEiqaH76kV_qEFXwE>

Hi Om Surushe,

You can now choose your channel’s handle.

As a reminder, in most cases, if you already have a  personalized URL  
<https://notifications.google.com/g/p/ACnX6LaL1myiP53XMVgnaZoUZ9xEmGNbCA_mFw6J4qQqs4nSHd-JLtCRcdjZUMYYTbDkRmSx484vj0VKYox6aRD9HcxHjllHm8hcL4BHMoopEStJOZLPj92IsTjmfJWnTwcx21qxDE5oTfgnVmZAPZXqY1jwn5rouA7Yc1xd9lcR6R6X>  
for your channel, we’ve reserved this for you as your handle. If you’re  
happy with that handle then you’re all set. If you want a different handle  
from the one we reserved, you can change it. If you don’t already have a  
personalized URL today, you’ll also be able to choose a handle. Keep in  
mind that handles are unique to each channel, so once a handle has been  
chosen, it can’t be selected by anyone else.

In the future, your handle will be how people mention you in comments,  
Community posts, and more.

Sincerely,
The YouTube team

To:


*Dear Sir / Madam, *


*Greetings of the day from LemonVB!*

*Wishing you all a very happy, prosperous, and healthy new year!*

We are pleased to inform you that we are looking for fresh and experienced
candidates for various posts in our organization.

*1. Jr. Engineer (For Freshers) with CTC of 8 lakhs/annum: Candidates from
a batch of 2023 are eligible to apply.*

*2. Sr. Engineer (Mechanical/ Automobile) with CTC 11 lakhs/annum: 4-5
years of experience in HVAC Design for Automobiles are eligible to apply. *

*For the past two years, we are hiring candidates for Jr. Engineer posts
through the Centralized recruitment process of LemonVB including the Online
aptitude test and further rounds. This year also we are continuing with the
same process. Eligible students can apply for the online aptitude test from
the official website of LemonVB. This can be considered an Off-Campus
Placement drive. *
However, the list of candidates who applied from your institute, results,
feedback, and more details during the selection process will be updated
through emails from time to time, if you don't mind.

*We are accepting applications only up to 15/01/2023.*

*Final Year BE/ B.Tech Students of all branches in the AY 2022-2023
(Passing out in 2023) are eligible for the Jr. Engineer post. *

*Candidates with a minimum of 4 Years of Experience in HVAC are eligible
for the Sr. Engineer post.*

   - *To apply for the Jr. Engineer post, interested students need to visit
   the “Careers” section of the official website of the LemonVB and find the
   link for filling out the application form
   “https://lemonvb.in/application-form-for-jr-engineer-2023/
   <https://lemonvb.in/application-form-for-jr-engineer-2023/>” provided in
   the last column of Job Box. The official website link is mentioned in the
   attachment. *
   - *For Sr. Engineer post applications are invited through Emails.
   Selection includes the shortlisting of the Resume followed by a Personal
   Interview.*
   - *For JD, selection procedure, job locations, and all other details it
   is recommended to read the "Detailed Advertisement of Recruitments
   2022-2023 LemonVB/DEC./2022/01" available in the Careers section on the
   official website.*
   - *It is also advised to go through the "FAQs regarding current
   recruitment at LemonVB" attached to this email. *

*We would be grateful if you share the information about the Centralized
Recruitment Drives at LemonVB with students of your esteemed institution.*
*You are requested to circulate this email and the attached documents with
details of the job to the students of BE / B.Tech of all branches (those
are in AY 2022-23, passing out in 2023) and alumni in contact. *

*we've included for you the attachments here Recruitment Posters and FAQ
Job Opening 2022-23. *

*For any queries feel free to contact us*


   - on General Helpline Number +91 8956 241 141 (Monday to Friday, 11 am
   to 5 pm),
   - Email: Ms. Pratima, HR Head -  head.hr@lemonvb.in and
   pratima.nimje.hr@lemonvb.in, Team LemonVB *-*  career@lemonvb.in (Queries
   from Emails will be answered "24×7").


*LEMONVB TECHSOLU PRIVATE LIMITED, is *a reputed Indian Startup by IITians
recognized by the DPIIT, registered Pvt Ltd company, and certified
Micro Enterprise (Services) by MSME. We are in the business of technical
advice, research and development, project management, design and
manufacturing of new products, and others as per client requirements. Visit
the official website to learn more details (About us, Team, Services,
Products, etc.).


*Please note that there are changes in the URL of the official website of
LemonVB and official contact IDs from Aug. 2022. The same was informed to
all clients through personal emails and made public via the official
Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter platforms of LemonVB.*

If you want to access the previous year's recruitment data for the Jr.
Engineer (2022 Batch) for reference, feel free to let us know.


*Please, acknowledge the receipt of this mail.*




*Thanks & Regards,*
*Team LemonVB*


*"Cutting-edge technological solutions and consultancy*
*to the challenges prevailing in various industries"*

snippet: Dear Students, Students are required to upload an image of themselves for their student I-cards & mark sheet. Please note that your student ID card & Mark sheet will be delayed if your uploaded
subject: Important Instruction regarding the Photographs for I-Cards and Marksheets
body:
Dear Students,

Students are required to upload an image of themselves for their student
I-cards & mark sheet.

Please note that your student ID card & Mark sheet will be delayed if your
uploaded photo does not meet the criteria set out in this document.

*Photo Guidelines*

You must submit a recent photograph (not older than 6 months). Failure to
upload a suitable photograph may result in payment of a fine for the issue
of your student ID card & Marks sheet. Poor quality and inappropriate
photos will not be printed.

The quality of your printed photos

*Your photo must be:*

•            clear and in focus

•            in colour

•            unaltered by computer software

What your printed photos must show

*Your photos must:*

•            be a close-up of your full head and upper shoulders

•            contain no other objects or people

•            be taken against a plain cream or light grey background

•            be in clear contrast to the background

•            not have ‘red eye’

*In your photo, you must:*

•            be facing forwards and looking straight at the camera

•            have a plain expression and your mouth closed

•            have your eyes open and visible

•            not have hair in front of your eyes

•            not have a head covering (unless it’s for religious or medical
reasons)

•            no hats or sunglasses

•            not have anything covering your face

•            not have any shadows on your face or behind you

•            The photo should be a colour, JPEG file

*-- *


*Thanking You,With regards,*

*Students' Section*
V*ishwakarma Institute of Technology,* Pune-37
*Phone - 020 - 24202252*

subject: Aspiring Minds - View AMCAT Report
body:
Dear Om Pravin Surushe,

        
        
        Congratulations on successfully taking AMCAT-India´s largest employability test. Tens of thousands of them secure their dream jobs each year through AMCAT.
        Your dream job is now only a few steps away:
        
        
    
       
        Link your Facebook account
         
        Download Feedback Report
         
        Prepare for interviews
         
        Your Dream Job
        
    
    
    
        
    
    
        
        myAMCAT.com provides you a host of services to prepare you for your upcoming placements. Our comprehensive resume guide,  placement tips, and career advice will help you secure your dream job.  Link  your Facebook to account to speed up your job search.
    
    
    
        Some exclusive features for you:
        
        Seven Stroke Feedback: A detailed seven page feedback report about your performance on various areas, tips to improve, and employability in various sectors is ready. Login to download your report.
        Free Public Profile: Now you can build your resume online and put up a complete public profile. The portal will allow you to share the public profile with companies in a professional manner.
       	
    
    
        
        
        Do not forget to study your detailed feedback report.Your feedback report tells you the areas in which you need to improve in order to succeed in the career of your choice. 
		Continue to work hard and we will try our best to find a job matching your profile. Our corporate client list is continuously growing with several of the largest companies across India currently hiring through AMCAT.

snippet: Studustry is giving you an opportunity to upgrade your professional profiles by asking questions to similar minded students and industry professionals! Don't wait.. join us today! Hello Thank you
subject: Come join Studustry's project based learning community for free!
body:
Studustry is giving you an opportunity to upgrade your professional profiles by asking questions to similar minded students and industry professionals! Don't wait.. join us today!

Hello 

Thank you for showing interest in for *Studustry!*

*As a part of rewarding people who have supported us during our initial phases, we are opening up the Studustry community specially for you.*

The Studustry community has a special channel on Discord ( https://discord.com/ ) which has students from all sectors participating in discussions with themselves and industry professionals who are willing to mentor young students. We also have faculty members as a part of this community!

Students can ask questions about their projects, internships and any other thing that builds their professional profiles and get them answered by other students or industry professionals!

Studustry team will also be posting all the project opportunities on Discord first! *And the best part?? It's absolutely free!*

As you all might already know, universities are now making project based learning a mandatory part of the curriculum and what better way to make yourself future-proof than joining a community about project based learning!

So, what are you waiting for! Click on the button below and join the Studustry community !

Join Studustry Discord Channel ( https://discord.gg/3HdxwDJ8 )

Studustry is a startup based in Pune & Aurangabad bringing the concept of project based learning to colleges in India. Look for our LinkedIn page to learn more about us.
Join the only project based learning community of India today by getting in touch with us.
Use this link if you would like to discuss anything in particular by directly chatting with us.

( https://www.facebook.com/studustry/ ) ( https://twitter.com/studustry?lang=en ) ( https://www.instagram.com/studustry/?hl=en ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/studustry/ )

Japan Career Program for First year and Second Year Students
 scheduled on 14th January 2023
body:
We have arranged the introductory session on 14th January, Saturday at
10:00 AM - 11:00 AM IST for 1st & 2nd Year Students.
Earlier our 9 students have successfully completed this Japan Career
Program.
*Interested student are requested to fill the form before joining the
introductory session : https://forms.gle/qUA9WFfehMexgXXUA
<https://forms.gle/qUA9WFfehMexgXXUA>*

Japan Career Program X VIT
Saturday, January 14 · 10:00 – 11:00am
Video call link: https://meet.google.com/agj-qkef-yhb


Please find attached document for the details of the *Japan Career
Program* which
includes four series:

Our Key Focus will be
1. Placements
2. Learning Japanese Language Level N5 - Level N4 ( Y 2023)
3. Exchange Program with Japanese University ( Sep 2023)
4. Education Tour ( April/Oct 2023) - Optional
5. Participation in YOUTH SDGs Summit ( March 2023)

*Codetots will offer platform which will have all Japanese companies
looking to recruit students based on study status & academic information.*
*If there is a match between the skill & interest of both the parties, it
will lead to smooth transition of work.*

The Japan Career Program is funded by JIWF <http://jiwf.org/> Association. We
are dedicated to offer unparalleled opportunities to students to reap out
maximum benefit out of this project. According to Nikkei Asia Japan races
to hire 250000 foreign engineers by 2025 as its already behind other
countries in nurturing IT Professionals indispensable to a digital
transformation. We aim to provide work integrated learning opportunities
and getting students out in the real world by enhancing the skills required
and boost employment prospect under the guidance of team from Japan & your
prestigious institute.


Thank you.

Yours Faithfully,
Prof. Dr. Swati Shilaskar

snippet: Dear Students , VERY IMP..... Sharing Notice again ..regarding RESEARCH PAPERS FOR JOURNAL PUBLICATION /PATENT 2020-21 BASED ON CAPSTONE PROJECT which was shared on 16/6/2021 on whatsapp Refer the PDF
subject:
DESH_RESEARCH PAPERS FOR JOURNAL PUBLICATION /PATENT 2020-21 BASED ON
 CAPSTONE PROJECT_JUNE 2021
body:
Dear Students ,

VERY IMP..... Sharing Notice again ..regarding RESEARCH PAPERS FOR JOURNAL
PUBLICATION /PATENT 2020-21 BASED ON CAPSTONE PROJECT which was shared on
16/6/2021 on whatsapp

Refer the PDF documents, Word document (Consent Letter format)...Go through
the notice carefully. Follow the steps as mentioned in the notice point
wise and do as instructed ....

1) As you have already been instructed by Hon. Director Sir, through
earlier notice, said that,  *all students must submit Research Papers /
Patent  based on  their Capstone Project 1 (CP1) projects in the required
format following the procedure as informed in the notice. *

2) Although sample Patent form, format is shared ,students are not aware
about its drafting, so for time being they can submit their Research Paper
for Patent if the students feel that their project leads to a product which
can be commercialized. However, they must select Patent instead of Research
Paper in the google form.

3) *All  CP1 group leaders  must ensure that you have submitted  your CP1
Guide with the word and PDF draft of the Research paper /Patent for his/her
review and to seek approval on it . Attach the Plagiarism report to it
 .Also inform your guide about  the tentative names* *of  Research Journals
/ Patents   which you have shortlisted for your Paper. Only after seeking
the approval on the paper /Patent  draft , tentative name of the journal
and  then on seeking your Guides consent.. you can upload your  CP1 paper
in the google form...*

4) Email the copy of the filled google form to your guide without fail.

5) Refer to the PDF copy of the google form to know the details to be
filled in it. If you face any query while filling the form or about the
documents plasese ask your Project Guide.

6) *All CRs ACRs will follow up and ensure Papers/ Patent  should  be
submitted  from all CP1 groups from their divisions. Ask respective CP1
group leaders from your division to update you once submission is done.... *


*Deadline to upload your Research Paper / Patent is extended to Thursday,
24th June 2021 by 11 pm...without fail....*


All the best ..

Dr. Sachin S. Sawant
Coordinator Capstone Project 1 & 2
Assistant Head R&D
Department of Engineering Sciences and Humanities (DESH)

snippet: For the students of Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, we are introducing a community of young and creative students who have innovative mindsets and yearn to learn new skills. AVINYA BHARAT is a
subject: =?UTF-8?Q?Skill_development_=7C_Community_for_VIT=C2=A0Students?=
body:
For the students of Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, we are 
introducing a community of young and creative students who have 
innovative mindsets and yearn to learn new skills. AVINYA BHARAT is a 
community comprising students and entrepreneurs.

Apply for the membership by registering on the following link: 
https://form.jotform.com/223236028556455

Why you should join?
I) Students get the opportunity to collaborate with thousands of 
students from different colleges and upskill themselves by getting free 
access to various courses and work on different projects with their 
inter-college or intra-college teams and also get associated with 
various startups. Access to various online and offline seminars, 
workshops, and events along with the best companies to get internship 
and placement offers. Along with learning, passes for some fun and 
amazing trips with the teams are also provided. They also get Networking 
opportunities in order to be in touch with CEOs of various companies.

Link: https://avinyabharat.com/index.php/member/

II) Entrepreneurs will get complete support to think of an idea or to 
convert their idea into revenue-generating models. They will get 
complete mentorship from idea validation, Company Formation, Incubation, 
and many more which will ultimately lead them toward the success of 
their startup. Along with this, they will get technical, marketing, 
funding, and workforce recruitment support.
They will also get free access to the best startup development courses 
in order to implement their idea flawlessly. They will also be given 
access to various online and offline seminars, workshops, and events in 
order to interact with industry experts, startup founders, and various 
companies to expand their network. Along with building their company, to 
refresh their minds, passes for some fun and amazing trips with the 
teams will also be provided.

Link: https://avinyabharat.com/index.php/entrepreneur/  [1]



Links:
------
[1] https://avinyabharat.com/index.php/entrepreneur/
