snippet: [Goldman Sachs] Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23 | Aptitude Test Powered by HackerRank Hi All, Thank you for registering for the Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23. Please find below
subject:
[Goldman Sachs] Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23 | Aptitude
 Test invitation
body:
[Goldman Sachs] Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23 | Aptitude Test - powered by HackerRank



  
    
      
        
        
          Hi All,

Thank you for registering for the Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23. Please find below your Aptitude Assessment details, scheduled on Sunday, 11th December 2022 at 4:00 pm: 

You have been invited to attend the challenge Engineering Campus Hiring Program 2022-23

We encourage you to bookmark & go through the test preparation instructions before you start the test and also advise you take this Sample Test to get comfortable with the test environment   

Please keep in mind the following instructions while attempting the test: 

- The link for the test will only go live at [4:00 PM] on 11th December 2022 and you will not be able to access the test before that.

- The login window will end at [04:30 PM] on 11th December 2022  and you will not be able to log into the test after this

- You will be required to fill in a form before the start of the test, please ensure you login 5 minutes before the registration close window 

- The duration of the test is 1 hour 30 minutes

- While the login window is 30 minutes, you will get 1 hour 30 mins from the time you start the test to complete the test

- Please ensure you are in a room with good connectivity for the entire duration of the test

- You will not be able to take the test via your phone and a laptop/desktop will be required

- There is only one attempt per registered email ID 

- DO NOT SHARE the test link with anyone as it will lead to disqualification

- Please be ready with a digital photo/copy of your College ID or a self-attested photograph and your resume as you would be required to upload the same at the time of the test

- You will need a video/web camera to attempt the test as the test is video proctored

- Please ensure the camera is facing directly at you and your face is visible at all times during the test. Also, ensure you are giving the test all by yourself and are in a well-lit room

- Any attempt at any sort of plagiarism will lead to disqualification

- Continue to review the FAQ for any queries related to this test

For any additional queries on the test please write to us at eventsupport@hackerrank.com or enggcampushiringprog@gs.com

We wish you all the best!

        
        
      
      
        
          Duration: 90 min
          
          
          Start Login Date/Time:
          
            11 Dec 2022 04:00 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
          
          End Login Date/Time: 11 Dec 2022 04:30 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
            Start Test
          
          You can also use
          this link
          to access the test
          
          anytime before the test expiry date above.
          Please check date and time in your time zone.
          
          
        
      
    
  


Please note once you begin the test the timer will start and the test cannot be paused. Hence it is highly recommended that you complete the test in one sitting.

In case of power failure or loss of internet connection, the test timer will continue to run even though you might not be attempting it, in such a case please contact us by replying back to this email.

For any technical queries, please refer to https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Fsections%2F115001822568-FAQs/EUKQHzUN/EDcI/o7riDnGyz0/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl or contact us at https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Frequests%2Fnew%3Fticket_form_id%3D360001035834./EkKQHzUN/EDcI/yhm3Q4634G/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl

HackerRank only provides a platform to conduct the tests. It does not schedule or evaluate any hiring tests or conduct interviews for any company. Hence for any of the above requests please contact the company that sent you the invite.

the Platform.

advantages and benefits of CD by clicking onto the link -

snippet: Dear Students, I request you to fill the Area of Interest, project Topics/Titles of projects (EDI/DAI/Major) and brief of project in 3-4 lines for Sem-II 2022-23 in the shared excel sheet (Classes are
subject:
To fill Project Topics/Titles of projects (EDI/Major Project) and
 brief of project.
body:
Dear Students,

I request you to fill the *Area of Interest*, *project Topics/Titles of
projects (EDI/DAI/Major) and brief of project in 3-4 lines for Sem-II
2022-23* in the shared excel sheet *(Classes are mentioned tab wise. Select
appropriate tab as per your class).*



*Note:*

·       One Member (Group Leader) of the group should fill the data.

·       Classes are mentioned tab wise. Select appropriate tab as per your
class


   - SYAI-A, SYAI-B, Btech-IT, SYMCA students need to enter complete data
   regarding your group formation and project related.
   - TY-IT, TYAI&DS-A, TYAI&DS-B classes need to follow groups as formed
   previously, so only mention your project related data.

·       Don’t delete/modify any Entry from the shared sheet.

·       Verify your PRN number, Roll number and name*(If PRN not mentioned
then add it) *


*Shared sheet Link:*

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Y1gYonlKHC8_IKRQKfex0lvbq_mOkCrq_KYhGXKL87E/edit?usp=sharing



*Guidelines for selecting project Topic:*

*1.    **The title should have an innovative idea.*

*2.    **It should have a social impact. *

*3.    **You should be able to publish your work in a conference or
journal. *

*4.    **Use a collaborative development platform like github to host your
project. *



*Fill the details in a shared sheet till 31/12/2022(Saturday), 06.00 pm.
Please consider this mail important and fill data on priority basis.*

*For Any Queries, feel free to contact me.*



Thanks and Regards
*Amruta. A. Mankawade*
*Assistant Professor,*
*Department of IT and Artificial Intelligence-Data Science.*
*VIT, Pune.*

snippet: Dear students Pls note 1. You all are having written exams at end semester for 60 marks in the offline mode except Final year students 2. There is No MSE MCQ exam except Final year students 3. MSE
subject: Information about examinations
body:
Dear students
Pls note

1. You all are having written exams at end semester for 60 marks in the
offline mode except Final year students
2. There is No MSE MCQ exam except Final year students
3. MSE reviews are scheduled in coming weeks only for PPT/GD, EDI/Major
project and internship
4 Pls refer assessment schemes shared in previous mail
5. Programming assessment schemes are applied only for specific course of
SY and TY class which is also mentioned in the previous mail attachment.
6. @Final year students pls note you all are having MSE MCQ based exams for
all OEs in the online mode

MSE review for Major project will be offline mode only.


Hope all your doubts are clear
I request if still any doubt pls meet me on Tuesday, meanwhile start
preparations on ppt or GD of all your courses, EDI proj, Maj proj.


@SY MCA students you will also have written exams at end semester
Same assessment pattern is applicable for all courses except HCI and
industry 4.0 subjects.

For these 2 subject concern faculty will inform you.

Subject: Introducing FE Mobility Leadership Challenge 2022 by Financial
Express
To: Sir / Ma'am <tpo@vit.edu>


The Financial Express is organising the Mobility Leadership Challenge. The
competition aims to tap into the Indian youth talent pool.
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=8230390598&e=9633a7e6e7>

Hello Sir/ Ma'am,

Greetings from Financial Express (Digital) team.

We are pleased to inform you that we are launching  the first edition of FE
Mobility Leadership Challenge (FE MLC), India’s leading hunt for the
brightest engineering and management talent, and would like to invite
students from your institute to register for India’s largest program that
identifies and rewards the brightest engineering & business minds in the
country.

*About FE Mobility Leadership Challenge (FE MLC)*
The Financial Express Digital is planning to launch the largest initiative
in India Inc to identify and reward bright young talent in the mobility
industry. FE Mobility Leadership Challenge, a programme that will tap into
the innermost desires of most engineering and management graduates to
fast-track their careers.

The program  is open to participation from engineering students who are
studying in the third or fourth year of an undergraduate engineering course
& all management students of the AICTE approved colleges. FE MLC 2022
consists of four phases:




*Phase 1: Call for Entries | Online Assessment Phase 2: Announcement of 1st
shortlist | Domain Test & Leadership Test Phase 3: Announcement of 2nd
shortlist | Online assessment of group dynamics and leadership Phase 4:
Announcement of 3rd shortlist | One-on-one interaction with India’s top
CXOs*

Each phase would be followed by a shortlisting process. The students who
move to Phase 4 will be interviewed by one of the leaders of India Inc on
the program’s Jury Panel.

*Why participate in FE MLC?*
India’s only platform that identifies the mobility talent through  industry
validated rigorous assessments and brings the talent in limelight by giving
them the recognition their talent deserves. The program gives the candidate
an exposure to a real-world scenario and makes them industry ready, while
evaluating them on parameters such as innovation and critical thinking
ability, giving their resume a validation. Thus, the program adds value to
a student’s career and gives a boost to their personality.

*How to participate?*
To participate, you have to register on our website www.femlc.com
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=d6f448577a&e=9633a7e6e7>
and complete the Phase 1 Assessment till 31st Oct 2022.

We also invite you to engage with the FE Careers community on:
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/FECareer
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=4ce8943b33&e=9633a7e6e7>
Linkedin - https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/fecareer
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=2bed067bf3&e=9633a7e6e7>
Instagram - https://instagram.com/fe_careers
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=64dc8bc435&e=9633a7e6e7>
Twitter - https://twitter.com/FECareer
<https://financialexpress.us5.list-manage.com/track/click?u=535372c39db4100a1ef33c602&id=805fd30ffb&e=9633a7e6e7>

We request you to share this email with the students of your esteemed
college and encourage them to participate in the program which will prove
to be a milestone in their academic journey.

Regards,
Financial Express
An IE Online Media Services Pvt Ltd Initiative

snippet: Dear all, Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering & Research (PCCOER) was established in the year 2014. The institute is well equipped with all the latest infrastructural facilities. PCCOER is
subject: PCCOER: Invitation for Navdhara 2k22
body:
Dear all,

Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering & Research (PCCOER) was established
in the year 2014. The institute is well equipped with all the latest
infrastructural facilities. PCCOER is having quality results in Savitribai
Phule Pune University, and has organised many events . 250+Patents and 150+
copyrights have been filed collectively by our students and faculty members.
Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering & Research (PCCOER) invites your
students to Navdhara 2k22 : State level project Competition.
We have organised an event called Navdhara on 23/09/2022, where we allow
first year students (currently second year) to showcase their projects
prepared in first year under PBL activity or any individual project.
Along with the price worth Rs 75,000/- , the best ones will get an
opportunity to earn one month internship with companies (our juries) such
as Tata motors, Copper Cloud, Xenstack, Builder Association of India and
many more. Students will also be guided for filling Patent and Copyright so
that they can protect their intellectual properties. NAVDHARA 2K22 event is
mainly created to increase the students confidence and explore themselves,
while building and presenting their project.
So we kindly request you to make your students participate and enrich the
event.

Download the broucher from the link-
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1yWxHgq1bKQiSf2MhhSSD_4Y54pz7sGZO/view

snippet: Next batch starting on 25th June! Become awesome! Join the Studustry community and get access to students across the world and also industry professionals across sectors! Hello Thank you for enrolling
subject: Slots filling up fast! Complete registration now!
body:
Next batch starting on 25th June! Become awesome! Join the Studustry community and get access to students across the world and also industry professionals across sectors!

Hello 

Thank you for enrolling for *Studustry's* unique *Experiential Learning Program!*

*We recently had a fascinatingly intriguing discussion session during the mid-way meeting for our first ELP batch and we would love it if you could be a part of the next batch and learn the ways of research, critical thinking, problem solving and group activities.*

We have received tremendous response for all of our batches and there are very few slots remaining for the the next one that is starting very soon. See below for details!
(Please disregard this email if you have already completed registration)

Use this link if you would like to discuss anything in particular by directly chatting with us with us about any questions at all!

*Emerging Technology in Auto Sector.*

Duration: 6 weeks
Start Date: 25th June (meetings every Sunday)
Last Date of Enrolment: 20th June

Who should participate?
-----------------------

- Students who wish to explore a new way of learning which is not governed by exams and assignments.
- Students who are willing to give 3-5 hrs in a week to work on the project
- Students who wish to have purposeful interaction with peers and industry professionals
- Students looking to have access to awesome industry projects from Studustry in the future

*We are giving a* *Special discount for Abhivriddhi Students*
Fees - Rs 500
To make sure you are serious about working on the project and do not leave midway while also making it easier for us to continue giving everyone a great learning experience

*Rewards* -
Connect with Industry Professionals to showcase your work and receive feedback
Receive a Certificate of participation
*Rewards worth Rs 2500 to students who do well*
Weekly thought-provoking sessions online
Access to Studustry Discord Community

Please click below to confirm your enrolment! Book fast! We have very limited slots for this!

Enroll ! ( https://rzp.io/l/autoelpvit )

Studustry is a startup based in Pune & Aurangabad bringing the concept of project based learning to colleges in India. Look for our LinkedIn page to learn more about us.

Dear Mam,
Kindly share with the registered students for the Zensar ESD program.
Following are the test details for the next step of the ESD program.

Students can take test from college or home should not be a problem.

Please read all the *Instructions* and the *PDF Document* given above.

*Assessment URL:* https://zensar.esd.hiringtests.in
<https://secure-web.cisco.com/1wKN0VSxcexYgS9iLrvB-P-Ai7qLNx5yxRAwk8c_fWNP95uTBnZORbW949h0O0pDdt5rHEKwcC2wAkC13xyyXu2Q5akHcAThfBYSnr5sWfzOzTZ8QXO_MKVt1LVZi1twU5cqn-QCW6Ew7aFlB28hhm1vswsUedb070yEQ6vV8drwG7eC_gnXd_Mbb5hkbFGNHmCvwSr_KIMxpoeev47N1D1ygqgVPGy2p7Gp6A6GX5nGHDhUrXav6uHxDfVesz07x8ty48Kn-v3PM8gMh4AnCEPF2D17_wpF48ypOilXk2mnnMkyJuqSXXGJtViO2dZhI93Oe5U4MC2zV8f-CXMK2A7k3ondQFy18hv6kBbMqyjk0z9niUlgbnkG8R2-2xedu2B29ZwlM30auWAM9OvMIyVfK2txzJlDrCgJV5UXCXOs/https%3A%2F%2Fzensar.esd.hiringtests.in%2F>
The link is active. Candidates can register and complete their profiles.

*System Check URL:* https://zensar.esd.hiringtests.in/Tests/test/deviceCheck
<https://secure-web.cisco.com/1LMQ02zZJYxVC2zmz-WjuC4CK5vM0QoZANlOFsUWAEmQ5HA1iwpudGQ_Q4_iSTWWZDM5toPSe5JkfH2EsyY67mb_5W1tQ_0iu3Mg7iD4pa_Q-FpPi9BNBvXLMN2vhuj2K4Vx10Mh6B06SvKvXZj2IFB6DJ-q5CfOXdahZQvDhbkVVzkzqgk0KMbCEFXRJ8FztFDyyobH-CU13GU4BCn8ALnYkm4tNBB113zYNKzGb8GlwNJhXieDusuEoKrE7gGOAi5xeCrw57xSE2JNssPnJeYqrhgdJ_P8HL47D9a0vdLGnAw28b_y5KuQRyUvo3Yi9mDfjUJVBg5jxxfVvT9mWJUFmFY49R7Qtv0QHc9SAHE4wDDDKVkzfHdkslHSfPq-RioUyobmAPmXN-B5jLSP9mgRf8TCb8hxgiLZXkuCsSUg/https%3A%2F%2Fzensar.esd.hiringtests.in%2FTests%2Ftest%2FdeviceCheck>
Please ask the candidates to take this System Check to check for any issues
before taking the assessment.

*Test Instructions for Candidate:*

   1. Click the *URL* to open the test page. Please go through the
   registration process and complete your profile to *100%*.
   2. After your profile is complete you will be redirected to the '*Available
   Tests*' page where you will type the *Test Code* provided in the text
   field and click on the '*Take Test*' button.
   3. The *Test Code* will be shared *5 minutes before* the assessment.
   4. The test consists of 2 sections, *Aptitude* and *English* (both
   sections are MCQ), and *no negative marking* for both sections.
   5. Aptitude has *30 MCQ* questions and the time to solve all of them is *40
   minutes*.
   6. English has *20 MCQ* questions and the time to solve all of them is *20
   minutes*.
   7. You will be asked for* camera (webcam)* permission, please '*Allow*'
   camera (webcam) access when prompted.
   8. The test starts in *fullscreen*, please do not exit fullscreen.
   9. *Do not close the Browser. Do not minimize the Browser Tab or Window.
   Do not open any new Browser Tab or Window. Do not click anywhere outside
   the Current Tab.*
   10. You can attempt the test sections in any order.
   11. Use only the buttons provided on the test screen, *do not use
   browser buttons like F5, Ctrl+R*.
   12. Once you have selected the test section you *CANNOT* return back to
   this page without completing the test section.
   13. The time does not get carried over from one section to another.
   14. If the time is over, your answers will be saved and the test will be
   submitted automatically.
   15. If the test stops for any technical reasons, it will resume from the
   same location where it was left last (your answers are saved and your time
   is saved).
   16. Disable your antivirus. Especially if your antivirus is Net
   Protector.
   17. If you are *not able *to go to the* Next or Previous *question*,
   check your internet connection*. The problem is in your network/internet.


Regards,
Amol Ashok Bhilare,
Assistant Professor,
Department of Computer Engineering,
Vishwakarma Institutes of Technology,Pune-411037

snippet: Dear author, We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY
subject: Final reminder 1 - Invitation for presentation registration in AOTA - 2023
body:
Dear author,

We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 9th January, 2023.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION AND COMMENTS IF APPLICABLE WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

<https://connect.ieee.org/NzU2LUdQSC04OTkAAAGH_Suo8RWUC3NOC49Kun_hC6rhoYzZOc2mQhiprUUnmilG99JIMzBo2V0qXWNk8iyXu1qwE2c=>

[Online Presentation slots will also be available]

IEEE IAS Global Conference on Renewable Energy and Hydrogen Technologies
(GlobConHT) is being organized on 11-12 March, 2023 at Male City, Maldives
with 100 % Financial Sponsorship of IEEE Industry Applications Society USA.

GlobConHT will provide an opportunity to the practicing engineers,
academicians and researchers to meet in a forum to discuss various issues
and its future direction of various Emerging Technologies of allied areas
of Industry Applications Society. The conference aims to put together the
experts from the relevant areas to disseminate their knowledge and
experience for the relevant future research scope. The conference is 100%
financially sponsored by IEEE Industry Application Society USA and
technically sponsored by eight top Universities across world. There are 10
tracks in the conference covering almost all areas of Industry Applications
Society.

Conference Tracks:
• Grid integration Challenges (system strength, voltage stability, inertia)
of Renewable Energy
• Energy Storage System Applications for Renewable Power Generation
• Power Electronic Applications for Renewable and Hydrogen Applications
• Hydrogen Generation, Storage and Transport Applications
• Hybrid and Remote Area Power Supply Systems
• Energy Assessment, Development, construction, Supply Chain and
Operational challenges of Renewable Energy Systems (Industry track)
• Offshore Wind Energy Applications
• Onshore Wind and Solar Applications
• Artificial Intelligence, Big Data, IoT, Block Chain Applications for
Renewable Energy Applications
• Economics of Renewable and Hydrogen Applications

Paper Submission Link: https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/GlobConHT2023
<https://connect.ieee.org/NzU2LUdQSC04OTkAAAGH_Suo8QnEbsgHx929nyBTmEbGn09MMkAVYBlnrRpdkpmvee9dWTIzbI_Zd1UGurb6b59JsDQ=>

Important Dates
Paper Submission Deadline: 15 November, 2022
Notification of Acceptance: 31 December, 2022
Regular Registration Due: 15 January, 2022
Conference Dates: 11-12 March, 2023

Call for Papers:
Original contributions based on the results of research and developments
are solicited. Prospective authors are requested to submit their papers in
not more than 6 pages, prepared in the two-column IEEE format. All the
accepted and presented papers will be eligible for submission to IEEE HQ
for publication in the form of e-proceedings in IEEE *Xplore*, which is
indexed with the world's leading Abstracting & Indexing (A&I) databases,
including ISI/SCOPUS/DBLP/EI-Compendex/Google Scholar.

All Accepted extended papers will be eligible for Submission to IEEE IAS
Transactions for further review.

snippet: Dear students, The registration timeline for code for good event is extended till 20th March 2022, 12 pm. Read all the instructions in the mail and register for the event . Thanks TPO team, VIT -------
subject:
Fwd: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Registration Process open
 for 2022 Software Engineer Program
body:
Dear students,
The registration timeline for code for good event is extended till 20th
March 2022, 12 pm.
Read all the instructions in the mail and register for the event .

Thanks
TPO team, VIT




---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Bagul, Jaishree <
Date: Thu, Mar 17, 2022 at 2:17 PM
Subject: RE: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Registration Process open
for 2022 Software Engineer Program
To:
Cc: Nandan Wahi, Priyanka <


Dear TPO,



This is to inform you that the registration timeline for Code for Good
event for Fulltime and Internship has been extended until 20th March, 2022
12:00 PM. We request you to kindly cascade this information to the student.
Also, please inform the students to* apply with the same email address
*provided
to us in the original sheet.

*Only the eligible students who register for the Code for Good via the link
will receive the assessment email*



Request you to kindly push for the registrations.



Regards,

Jaishree



--------------------------------

 Dear All,



The registration process for the Code For Good 2022 is now open!



Please share the below registration details and the attached JD with your
students and ask them to submit their formal application for the Software
Engineer Program on our Careers page at the earliest*.*



*Please Note: The Code For Good event is the only way this year by which
the students can apply for the Software Engineer Program (SEP) at JP Morgan
Chase & Co. Hence, I request you to urge all eligible students to register
themselves for the Code For Good 2022 at the earliest.*



*Eligibility Criteria for registration for the Software Engineer Program:*

   - *Degrees:* B.Tech./B.E./MCA
   - 2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
   - 2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
   - *Streams or Specializations:* Computer Science/Information Science/
   Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
   Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
   - A well-rounded academic background with *minimum aggregate 7 CGPA
   [until date] in engineering course*



*Registration Links:*

   - The students from the 2023 graduating batch, who are applying for the
   Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, should click here
   <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210245503/?utm_medium=jobshare>
to
   register themselves.
   - The students from the 2024 graduating batch, who are applying for the
   Internship opportunity in 2023, should click here
   <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210247021/?utm_medium=jobshare>
to
   register themselves.



*Registration Dates:*

   - The last day for registration for students from the 2024 graduating
   batch, who are applying for the Internship opportunity in 2023, is
16th March
   2022.
   - The last day for registration for students from the 2023 graduating
   batch, who are applying for the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, is 16
   th March 2022.



*Selection Process:*

   - Eligible students register themselves on the JP Morgan Chase Careers
   page as per the given deadlines [as mentioned above].
   - All eligible students appear for an online coding test. We will share
   further details on the online tests at a later stage.
   - All eligible students appear for a video interview
   - JP Morgan Chase announces the final participant shortlist for the Code
   For Good events



*Important Points to Know:*

   1. Click ‘Apply Now’ and sign in with your JPMC career site username and
   associated personal email address. In case of you have previously signed up
   with your college email address, please edit the email address to your
   personal one before proceeding with this application. If you do not recall
   your password click forgot your password and follow the instructions
   2. Complete your application. If you are currently using an ‘.edu’ email
   address please update it to a personal non ‘.edu’ email address. Failure to
   do so could cause delays in you receiving updates regarding your candidacy.
   You will be required to attach your resume with a Photograph on the
   right-hand/left-hand corner [Mandatory], kindly update your prior
   internship experience with other skills [optional].
   3. In case your campus does not appear in the application form, please
   select ‘other’ and mention the campus in the free text field.
   4. Click “Submit” to officially submit your application – a confirmation
   will be sent to the email address on your account when your application has
   been received

body:
#

[["Analytics Vidhya"]]

#

JOB-A-THON
(India's Largest Data Science Hiring Event)
10+ Companies are waiting for you!

#

At JOB-A-THON, data science enthusiasts, freshers, and professionals get the opportunity to showcase their skills and get a chance to interview with top companies for leading job roles in data science, machine learning & analytics.

snippet: Dear author, Your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION
subject:
LAST REMINDER - Invitation for registration and presentation in AOTA - 2023
  (Registration deadline: 15th January, 2023) - (THERE WILL BE NO FURTHER
  EXTENSIONS UNDER ANY CIRCUMTANCES)
body:
Dear author,

Your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 15th January, 2023. THERE WILL BE NO FURTHER EXTENSIONS UNDER ANY CIRCUMTANCES.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION AND COMMENTS IF APPLICABLE WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

snippet: NVIDIA Software Engineer 6M Intern Hiring Test - 20 Jan 2023 Powered by HackerRank Hey There! Hope you are doing well and keeping safe. You have come a long way and we are very pleased to send you the
subject:
Test Invites - NVIDIA System Software Engineer Hiring Test - 20
 January 2023
body:
NVIDIA Software Engineer 6M Intern Hiring Test - 20 Jan 2023 - powered by HackerRank



  
    
      
        
        
          

 

Hey There!

Hope you are doing well and keeping safe. 

You have come a long way and we are very pleased to send you the invite for NVIDIA System Software Intern Hiring - 20th January 2023. As part of the assessment process, there would be a test followed by interviews for shortlisted candidates.

The technical screening test will be held on Friday, 20th January 2023  

Please note that the test log-in is valid for 30 minutes starting 5:00 PM

To ensure that you do not lose time while logging in to start the test, we recommend you fill the registration required for the test before the test login i.e. 5:30 PM. While registering, please ensure to keep the resume handy for uploading.

We have some information about the test which we think might be useful:


	This is a 60-minute test 
	The test would focus on Analytical/Problem solving, Programming/Coding, Data Structures and OS


 

Wish You all the best!!

 NVIDIA University Relations

        
        
      
      
        
          Duration: 60 min
          
          
          Start Login Date/Time:
          
            20 Jan 2023 05:00 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
          
          End Login Date/Time: 20 Jan 2023 05:30 PM IST
            
            (Asia - Kolkata)
            
          
          
          
            Start Test
          
          You can also use
          this link
          to access the test
          
          anytime before the test expiry date above.
          Please check date and time in your time zone.
          
          
        
      
    
  


Please note once you begin the test the timer will start and the test cannot be paused. Hence it is highly recommended that you complete the test in one sitting.

In case of power failure or loss of internet connection, the test timer will continue to run even though you might not be attempting it, in such a case please contact us by replying back to this email.

For any technical queries, please refer to https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Fsections%2F115001822568-FAQs/43RH6TYN/EDcI/Wz0et-ejI6/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl or contact us at https://click.pstmrk.it/2tsm/support.hackerrank.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Frequests%2Fnew%3Fticket_form_id%3D360001035834./5HRH6TYN/EDcI/eW9WZ_qE6L/aHJ3LXRlc3QtaW52aXRl

HackerRank only provides a platform to conduct the tests. It does not schedule or evaluate any hiring tests or conduct interviews for any company. Hence for any of the above requests please contact the company that sent you the invite.

snippet: Dear Students, EDI/DAI/Major Project review -I is scheduled on 6th and 7th October, 2021 from 10 am to 6 pm. Instructions: · The students will be evaluated by their respective Guide along with a Jury
subject: MID SEM REVIEW for EDI/DAI/Major Project
body:
Dear Students,
*EDI/DAI/Major Project review -I is scheduled on 6th and 7th October, 2021
from 10 am to 6 pm.*

*Instructions:*



·       *The students will be evaluated by their respective Guide along
with a Jury from the department.* *All the groups under the guidance of
Jury 1 and Jury 2 need to report according to the slot provided in
timetable in respective location.*



·       *The review will be conducted offline in respective Labs. Please
find the schedule of timetable in attachment provided below.*



·       Time for presentation is 10-15 Min and 5 min of Question Answer.



·       7 to 10 slides for a project presentation are expected.


*Note:* For any different component if any exam is scheduled (between
project review timing) then you need to prior inform your guides and get
your review done on the same day.



*Contents:*

1.            Title

2.            Aim

3.            Objectives

4.            Problem Statement

5.            Scope of Project

6.            Feasibility of Project

7.            Front End, Back End, Database, Algorithm

8.            Hardware Used (if any)

9.            Literature review

10.         Proposed Diagram

11.         Conclusion

12.         References



*                         Format for Mid Semester Assessment*

Mid-Semester Assessment  will be of 50 Marks to be converted to 30 Marks.



*Sr. No.*

*Parameter*

*Marks*

1

Problem Statement

10

2

Literature Review

10

3

Group formation and Identification of individual responsibility

10

4

Objective of Project Activity

10

5

Knowledge of domain, Latest technology and modern tools used /to be used

10



*TOTAL*

*50*



For Any Queries, Feel free to contact me.


Thanks and Regards
*Amruta. A. Mankawade*
*Assistant Professor,*
*Department of IT and Artificial Intelligence-Data Science.*
*VIT, Pune.*

snippet: Greetings from Team VishwaConclave!!✨ VishwaConclave is back to give you an enriched start for the year 2023. We are delighted to announce an interactive session with Vice Adm. Raman Puri (Retd.) PVSM,
subject: [IMPORTANT] Walk-in Registrations open at 10:30 AM
body:
*Greetings from Team VishwaConclave!!✨*



VishwaConclave is back to give you an enriched start for the year 2023. We
are delighted to announce an interactive session with *Vice Adm. Raman Puri
(Retd.) PVSM, AVSM, VSM.* He served in a number of important positions
during his career. These include a Destroyer and a Carrier Command, Founder
Director of the College of Naval Warfare, Director Staff Requirements
(NHQ), the Flag Officer Offshore Defence Advisory Group (FODAG), Flag
Officer Maharashtra Naval Area (FOMA). He is also an alumnus of the Command
and General Staff College from the erstwhile USSR and the National Defence
College, New Delhi. In the career span of 40 years, he has been the
Commander of 5 frontline warships of the Indian Navy including the Aircraft
Carrier INS Vikrant.

*The session will be based on  agendas as follows : *

1. Maritime Heritage & Naval Prowess.
2. Strategic Importance of Indo-Pacific Relations.
3. India’s National Security and Strategization Framework.
4. Citizens' duties in the face of national threats.

*Be ready for an exquisite experience and thought-provoking session.*

*Join us on:*

*Date: 16th January 2023*

*Day: Monday*

*Time: 11:00 am onwards*

*Venue: Sharad Arena, VIT, Pune*

Register Now! <https://bit.ly/3Zso8hN>

snippet: Advisory Notifications will be Generally Available as of November 17, 2022. MY CONSOLE You are receiving this notification because you are a(n) Project Owner in an organization. Hello Surushe, We'
subject:
[Update] For GCP Organizations, all Security and Privacy
 Notifications will be sent through Advisory Notifications
body:
Advisory Notifications will be Generally Available as of November 17, 2022.




Google Cloud Platform



MY CONSOLE




You are receiving this notification because you are a(n) Project Owner in  
an organization.

Hello Surushe,

We're writing to let you know that Advisory Notifications will become  
Generally Available as of November 17, 2022. This means that your  
Organization will gradually stop receiving the traditional notification  
email about critical security and privacy issues with full text and any  
attachments.

Your Organization will only receive the Advisory Notifications email. You  
will then have to log into the Google Cloud console to view the issue's  
details and attachments. You can find an example of the Advisory  
Notifications email below:



Advisory Notifications email
What do I need to know?

Advisory Notifications delivers targeted communications about critical  
security and privacy issues in the Google Cloud Console. Advisory  
Notifications helps your Organization:


Prioritize responses to critical security and privacy events
Understand the details of the event
Securely download any accompanying data through a secure portal
Configure who receives notifications through integration with Essential  
Contacts

What do I need to do?

If you haven't already done so:


Visit Managing Contacts for Notifications to learn how to configure your  
Essential Contacts Security and All groups to receive email alerts of  
Advisory Notifications.
Visit the Viewing Advisory Notifications Quickstart Guide to learn how to  
grant select users the required roles and IAM permissions to see  
notification details and download attachments.

We're here to help

If you have any questions or would like to learn more about viewing  
advisory notifications, please visit our support page.

Thanks for choosing Google Cloud.





–The Google Cloud Team

SUPPORT




Was this information helpful?

Cloud on Twitter

important changes to Google Cloud Platform or your account.

snippet: What's new? It's Thursday, and you know what that means! Here's a list of the stuff we shipped during the past weeks: Lifecycle Jobs In this repository, Romaric shows you several ways you
subject: Qovery | Lifecycle Jobs, Cronjobs, Last Goodbye to the V2...
body:
What's new? 
 It's Thursday, and you know what that means! Here's a list of the stuff we shipped during the past weeks: 
 
 Lifecycle Jobs 
 In this repository, Romaric shows you several ways you can use Lifecycle Jobs, which include: 
 - Call HTTP endpoint when an Environment is created 
- Create and Destroy an AWS RDS instance with Terraform 
- Create and Destroy an AWS Lambda with Serverless 
- Create and Destroy an AWS EC2 instance with Pulumi 
 Lifecycle jobs run on a Kubernetes cluster and are executed only when a specified event occurs in the environment. The output files created by the job will be automatically set as environment variables for services within the same environment. These types of jobs are useful for tasks such as seeding a database or creating external resources not natively managed by Qovery. 
 Qovery allows you to create and deploy jobs from Git Repository or Container Registry. 
 [Image "6f5f8b38-8dff-4c63-bf90-1650059094eb_Screenshot+2023-01-03+at+16.19.36.png?auto=compress,format"] 
 
 
 Cronjobs 
 Alessandro, Lead Product Manager at Qovery, joined me during our November Demo Day to talk about Cronjobs, as it was highly expected by most of you. While the development of this feature just started then, I have the honour to inform you that Cronjobs are now available! 🤩 
 A cronjob is a type of workload that runs on a Kubernetes cluster on a regular schedule. It can be used to execute tasks on a regular basis, such as pulling data from an external service every hour or processing data in a database. Qovery allows users to create and deploy Cronjobs from either a Git repository or a container registry. 
 To know more about it, check out our documentation! 
 [Image "5d022e81-f59a-429c-b003-338624bffe59_Screenshot+2023-01-03+at+16.18.59.png?auto=compress,format"] 
 
 Read the full changelog 
 You can reply to this email with thoughts/feedback on the changes we're making, or even better, join us on our Discord! 
 Regards, Albane from the Qovery team.

snippet: Dear Students, Application form for both, the Core Committee and Non Core Committee of Event Planning and Execution Committee (EPEC) AY 2021-22 are given in the respective links below. Interested
subject: Fwd: Application form for Event Planning and Execution Committee 2021-2022
body:
Dear Students,

Application form for both, the Core Committee and Non Core Committee of
Event Planning and Execution Committee (EPEC) A.Y. 2021-22 are given in the
respective links below. Interested students should fill the Google form
before *28th June 2021 (Monday) 11:59pm.*

Link for Core Committee:
https://forms.gle/YYiGyVwk2cdPnUCN7


Link for Non Core Committee:
https://forms.gle/JpNUS5fwJPaZxdvF6

The interviews for the post of Chairperson & Mentor are scheduled on *3rd
July & 4th July 2021* so all the applicants of the respective posts should
compulsorily refer the prerequisite task attached to the mail & should be
ready on the mentioned date of Interview. Further details will be notified
soon to respective applicants.


Dean-Student Activities

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Ananya Pandey <7ananyapandey7.cqiitkgp@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, Oct 13, 2022 at 5:05 PM
Subject: All India Placement Aptitude Test | Communiqué IIT Kharagpur
To:



Greetings from Communiqué IIT Kharagpur



Communiqué IIT Kharagpur brings you an All India Placement Aptitude Test to
prepare final year/pre-final year students for the upcoming
Placement/Internship season. The Test will have two sections to hone your
aptitude skills.



[image: 🎯] Round 1: General Aptitude Test

[image: 🎯] Round 2: Company-Wise Aptitude Test

Who can give this test?

Anyone with a zeal to solve interesting and challenging aptitude questions
can give the test [image: 😎]



Registration Link:
https://unstop.com/quiz/all-india-placement-aptitude-test-indian-institute-of-technology-iit-kharagpur-455508



Deadline: 16th Oct 2021 (11:59 pm)



Why should you give this Test?

[image: 📌] The test will Increase Problem Solving and Critical thinking
skills.

[image: 📌] The test will make students comfortable with the test pattern
of different companies and will increase the chances of selection.

[image: 📌]The test will check candidates' thinking, verbal, and
observational skills and help them evaluate where they are lacking.

[image: 📌] Cash Prize worth 3,000 and Assured Goodies to every college
winner having more than 100 registration.



About Us:

Communiqué is the official soft skills and personality development society
of the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT), Kharagpur campus working under
the aegis of the Vice President, Technology Students Gymkhana. It was
founded in the year 2006 by our distinguished alumni Anindya Dutta to aid
in the development of soft skills & personality among the KGP community.


For any queries/doubts, you can ping us at cq.iitkharagpur@gmail.com
[image: image.png]



-- 

Regards,

Ananya Pandey

Secretary

Communiqué

IIT Kharagpur

7ananyapandey7@gmail.com

Mobile: 7499289654

snippet: Social Welfare & Development Committee HDFC Badhte Kadam Scholarship for Professional Graduation Students 2022-23 Scholarship aims to provide financial assistance to students to continue and
subject:
[IMPORTANT] HDFC Badhte Kadam Scholarship for Professional Graduation
 Students 2022-23
body:
New Template
Social Welfare & Development Committee

*HDFC Badhte Kadam Scholarship for Professional Graduation Students 2022-23*

Scholarship aims to provide financial assistance to students to continue
and complete their education. In addition, in due course, the program will
also offer selected candidates additional support which could include
mentorship and access to career counselling programmes.


*Deadline : *30th Sept., 2022

*Eligibility :  *

• Open for students who have passed Class 12 and who are currently pursuing
general graduation courses (any year) such as BTech, MBBS, B.Arch, etc. in
recognized colleges or universities in India.
• Applicants must have obtained at least 60% marks in the previous class or
board exams.
• Annual family income of the applicants should be below INR 6,00,000, from
all sources.
• Special consideration will be given to -
1) Girl students
2) Students who are going through any kind of crisis.
• Children of employees of HDFC & Buddy4Study are not eligible.
• Students from pan-India are eligible.

*Benefits:*

INR 100,000
Note: Scholarship funds can be utilized only for academic expense purposes
which include tuition fees, exam fees, books, stationery, online learning,
and payment of internet/data pack bills

*Documents :*

• Passport size photograph
• Marksheet of previous education qualification
• A government-issued identity proof (Aadhaar Card/Voter ID/Driving
License/PAN Card)
• Current year admission proof (Fee Receipt/Admission Letter/Institution ID
Card/Bonafide Certificate)
• Applicant Bank Passbook/Cancelled Cheque (Information will also be
captured in the application form)
• Income Proof
• Proof of family/personal crisis (if applicable)
Apply Here
<https://www.buddy4study.com/page/hdfc-ltds-badhte-kadam-scholarship>

*Social Welfare & Development Committee*

Pushkar Helge: 7756885249

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Pankaj Kunekar <pankajkunekar30@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, Jan 17, 2023 at 3:38 PM
Subject: Fwd: Call for Papers_ICORE-2023_International Congress on
Renewable Energy and RE/EV Industrial Expo_10-12 March-2023
To: <pankaj.kunekar@vit.edu>




---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Nitin Mawale <npmawale@aissmscoe.com>
Date: Mon, 16 Jan 2023 at 21:36
Subject: Call for Papers_ICORE-2023_International Congress on Renewable
Energy and RE/EV Industrial Expo_10-12 March-2023
To: Nitin Mawale <npmawale@aissmscoe.com>


*Dear Sir/Madam**,*



*PFA. ICORE-2023 Brochure.*


The All India Shri Shivaji Memorial Society (AISSMS) was established in
1917 by Late H H Shrimant Shri Shahu Chhatrapati Maharaj of Kolhapur to
promote the noble cause of education. The AISSM Society is dedicated to the
noble cause of military, general, technical and management education in
India. Twenty Institutions are under the ambit of the society. The society
management is very pragmatic and progressive. The AISSMS COE, Pune is a
co-education Institute established in 1992. The College of Engineering is
affiliated to the Savitribai Phule Pune University (SPPU), Pune. AISSMS COE
conducts AICTE approved courses leading to the degree of Bachelor of
Engineering (BE) in 8 engineering streams and Master of Engineering (ME) in
7 Engineering streams and 4 PhD programs. AISSMSCOE is Accredited *NAAC
with “A+” Grade *and awarded as *“Best Engineering College” *in the Urban
region in 2019-20 by SPPU Pune.

Solar Energy Society of India *(SESI)*, established in1976 with its
Secretariat in New Delhi, is the Indian Section of the International Solar
Energy Society *(ISES)*. SESI is a multi-faceted national membership
organization. With its long history and extensive technical and scientific
expertise provided by its members, the Society is amodern, future oriented
Non-Governmental Organization (NGO). SESI has been serving the needs of the
Renewable Energy community and the Society supports its members in the
advancement of Renewable Energy Technological, Implementation and
Education. The objectives of SESI are to Advance, Promote and Propagate the
use of Renewable Energy by Encouraging Basic and Applied Research in
Renewable Energy.





The aim of this ICORE-2023 is to provide an allied platform for emerging
and recent trends in Renewable Energy and Electric Vehicles. Prospective
authors are requested to submit their papers in the double column IEEE
conference template, maximum 6 pages and abstract within 300 words.



*Accepted and presented papers will be forwarded for the inclusion in
SCOPUS indexed Renewable Energy Journal.*

*TRACKS*

*Track-1*

§ *Role of Renewable Energy for Creating A Sustainable and Self Reliant
India*

§ *Role of Renewable Energy in Engineering Education*

§ *Recent Trends in Renewable Energy*

§ *Impact of Renewable Energy on Industry and Society *

§ *Sustainable Renewable Energy Technologies*

§ *Food Sustainability and Energy Management*

*Track-2*

§ *Communication Technologies for Smart Grid*

§ *EV Technologies and Battery Management*

§ *Automation, Smart Sensors and Metering*

*Track-3*

§ *Computational Techniques in Renewable Energy*

§ *Green Computing*

*Track-4*

§ *Monitoring,ProtectionandControlinEnergySystems*

§ *EnergyManagementinPowerSector*

§ *PowerElectronicsandGrid Interface*

§ *Advanced Power Converter Topologies*

§ *Waste Management and Energy Conservation*

§ *Smart Energy Storage*

*Track-5*

§ *Demand, Response, Smart/Green Buildings and Home Automation*

§ *Renewable Energy Technology and Environment*

§ *Nano Technology Applications to Renewable Energy*

§ *Smart Materials,Photonics Material/Technologyfor Solar Energy*

§ *Thin Film Technology*

§ *AnyotherrelevanttotheConferenceTheme*

subject: DataSolve Hackathon by - Wolters Kluwer
body:
Dear Students,

Register for DataSolve hackathon.

DataSolve registration link
<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fforms.office.com%2Fr%2FPjxBCB9rWJ&data=05%7C01%7CVibha.Bathla%40wolterskluwer.com%7Ca3d0ab4bb7594b43d76f08dab7dc9963%7C8ac76c91e7f141ffa89c3553b2da2c17%7C0%7C0%7C638024455351175110%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=EnowJpc1KTQ%2F3%2Bd1wZZPMw7BvZqbx0Q%2BY6gWaO24PO4%3D&reserved=0>
– Click on this link for DataSolve registration and note that the same link
is also present in the brochure.





  Below is a brief and the schedule for the hackathon event- *DataSolve*.



About Datasolve

DataSolve gives you the chance to work with engineers and data scientists
to share insights and better understand real-world opportunities available
to you in the field of data science. The two-week hackathon-style
competition is an annual event conducted across multiple geographies with
the goal of connecting you to Wolters Kluwer executives through your shared
ideas, experiences and passion for using data to solve real-world
challenges.



Key Dates:



Problem statement released and Kaggle competition link provided to
participants

14th Nov 22

Students submit answers to challenge and results are updated real time on
the leaderboard

14th Nov 22 - 25th Nov 22

Top 3 teams will be notified and asked to create a presentation explaining
their solution

28th Nov 22 - 30th Nov 22

Students are invited to Wolters Kluwer in Kalyani nagar, Pune office to
present. Winners are announced and a celebration event to follow

15th Dec- 9 am till 12 pm



The winning teams will be awarded prizes worth *1.2Lakhs.*





<https://nam04.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolterskluwer.com%2Fen&data=05%7C01%7CVibha.Bathla%40wolterskluwer.com%7Cf5ef274255484bb18ada08dab2b3a63d%7C8ac76c91e7f141ffa89c3553b2da2c17%7C0%7C0%7C638018781925935348%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=KA%2BDtGE0QaT5d1f6gDZwhBYja9e2h19rGXK4v71pF8U%3D&reserved=0>

*About Wolters Kluwer*

Wolters Kluwer (WKL) is a global leader in professional information,
software solutions, and services for the health, tax & accounting, finance,
risk & compliance, and legal sectors. We help our customers make critical
decisions every day by providing expert solutions that combine deep domain
knowledge with advanced technology and services. Wolters Kluwer reported
2018 annual revenues of €4.3 billion. The group serves customers in over
180 countries, maintains operations in over 40 countries, and employs
approximately 19,000 people worldwide. The company is headquartered in
Alphen aan den Rijn, the Netherlands. Wolters Kluwer shares are listed on
Euronext Amsterdam (WKL) and are included in the AEX and Euronext 100

body:
Dear all,

I am writing this mail on behalf of the Head, IT department.
Semester 2 has started from 2nd Jan 2023 and it is observed that maximum
students have not reported to college. *Strict action* will be taken

students to report to college immediately.

Thanks and Regards

snippet: Greetings Everyone, CSI VIT Pune Student Branch is thrilled to announce its upcoming C++ workshop, which will begin on 20th January and teach you everything from scratch. Perks of C++ Workshop: Free
subject: Last 24 hours left for registration of C++ Workshop!!
body:
Greetings Everyone,

CSI VIT Pune Student Branch is thrilled to announce its upcoming C++
workshop, which will begin on 20th January and teach you everything from
scratch.

Perks of C++ Workshop:

   - Free Certification
   - No prior Knowledge Required
   - Hands-on implementation and guidance
   - Good and Conceptual understanding of Object Oriented Programming


What You Will Learn

   - The Fundamentals of C++
   - Write fast and powerful C++ programs, compile the source code, and
   create executable files.
   - Learn Object-Oriented Programming Design Concept in C++ Perfectly with
   Examples
   - Learn best practices and avoid pitfalls via useful Do’s and Don’ts
   - Learn C++ features that allow you to program compact and
   high-performance C++ applications

Register Now ! <https://forms.gle/VNKKozgjR8gkL7br5>

body:

Dear Developer,

Your Google Cloud project winged-odyssey-325007 was shut down on January  
17, 2023 7:24:19 PM UTC.

Shut-down projects and the data stored in them may be recovered for a  
limited time before the projects are permanently deleted. If you'd like to  
recover your project, you must cancel the project's permanent deletion  
before February 16, 2023 7:24:19 PM UTC.

To recover your shut-down project:

Visit the Resources pending deletion page.
Select the project you want to recover, and click Restore.
In the confirmation dialog, click Restore.


If you cannot recover your project by following the instructions above, you  
can try restoring it using the gcloud undelete command.

If you take no action by February 16, 2023 7:24:19 PM UTC, you will be  
unable to recover your project.

snippet: THE TEST DEADLINE IS EXTENDED TO 23RD MARCH 2022, 8AM. REGISTRATION PROCESS IS CLOSED. READ THE MAIL BELOW COMPLETELY. ------------------ K, Karthik S Mar 21, 2022, 8:56 PM (12 hours ago) to Priyanka,
subject: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Hacker rank test DEADLINE IS EXTENDED
body:
THE TEST DEADLINE IS EXTENDED TO 23RD MARCH 2022, 8AM.
REGISTRATION PROCESS IS CLOSED.
READ THE MAIL BELOW COMPLETELY.

------------------
K, Karthik S
Mar 21, 2022, 8:56 PM (12 hours ago)
to Priyanka, Jaishree, Sherry

Dear All,



Thank you for your continuous support to campus hiring at JP Morgan Chase &
Co.!



We have received multiple mails and queries regarding issues with the test
links. In view of this situation, we have *extended the test deadline to
23rd March 2022, 8 AM IST**.*



*The registrations for the process are closed*. All the students who have
applied on or before 20th March will get the test links in batches. Please
cascade the same to the students. We will keep you posted on the further
updates.





*Regards,*

*Karthik*


-----------------

On Thu, Mar 17, 2022 at 3:52 PM TPO - Vishwakarma Institute of Technology,
Pune <tpo_students@vit.edu> wrote:

> Dear J P Morgan Registered,
>
> Please  go through below mail received from the company :
> -------------------------
>
> Greetings from JP Morgan Chase & Co.!
>
>
>
>    - *Online Test Date & Time : 18th March 2022 (Friday) at 8.00 AM IST
>    for both Full-time and Internship hiring process*
>    - *Test link will be received directly on the registered mail id of
>    the candidate*
>
>
>
> Please find below *important instructions for the** online coding test* with
> respect to the Software Engineer Program [SEP] selection process. Please
> share the same with all eligible and interested students* :*
>
>
>
>    - The online coding test is the first step in the SEP selection process
>    - We will use the *HackerRank* platform to conduct the test
>    - *Students can start the test between 18th March 2022 8 AM IST till
>    21st March 2022 8 AM IST.* Students will not be able to access the
>    test outside of this time window.
>    - This is a programming test of 100 marks having 2 programming
>    questions carrying 50 marks each.
>    - There is no negative marking; the students should try to attempt all
>    questions
>    - The time allowed for this test is 60 Minutes. The students can
>    revisit the questions any number of times
>    - *Switching between tabs,* *while attempting the test,* *is
>    considered a violation and is, hence, not allowed*
>    - *The test is proctored.* Copying from others or trying to look for
>    solutions over the web is prohibited and will lead to rejection of
>    candidature
>    - *The students will be allowed to start the test only after they have
>    switched on their webcam*
>    - Before starting the test, the students have been asked to mention a
>    few personal details [Name, email ID etc.]. *They should enter the
>    same details that they have used to apply for the Software Engineer Program
>    on the JP Morgan Chase & Co. Careers page.*
>    - For queries related to HackerRank test or the platform please mail -
>    hackerrank.support.cases@jpmchase.com
>
>
> -------------------------
> All the best!
> Thanks.
> A.S. Mitragotri
> TPO,
> VIT
>
> On Thu, Mar 17, 2022 at 3:08 PM TPO - Vishwakarma Institute of Technology,
> Pune <tpo_students@vit.edu> wrote:
>
>> Dear students,
>> The registration timeline for code for good event is extended till 20th
>> March 2022, 12 pm.
>> Read all the instructions in the mail and register for the event .
>>
>> Thanks
>> TPO team, VIT
>>
>>
>>
>>
>> ---------- Forwarded message ---------
>> From: Bagul, Jaishree <
>> Date: Thu, Mar 17, 2022 at 2:17 PM
>> Subject: RE: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Registration Process
>> open for 2022 Software Engineer Program
>> To:
>> Cc: Nandan Wahi, Priyanka <
>>
>>
>> Dear TPO,
>>
>>
>>
>> This is to inform you that the registration timeline for Code for Good
>> event for Fulltime and Internship has been extended until 20th March,
>> 2022 12:00 PM. We request you to kindly cascade this information to the
>> student. Also, please inform the students to* apply with the same email
>> address *provided to us in the original sheet.
>>
>> *Only the eligible students who register for the Code for Good via the
>> link will receive the assessment email*
>>
>>
>>
>> Request you to kindly push for the registrations.
>>
>>
>>
>> Regards,
>>
>> Jaishree
>>
>>
>>
>> --------------------------------
>>
>>  Dear All,
>>
>>
>>
>> The registration process for the Code For Good 2022 is now open!
>>
>>
>>
>> Please share the below registration details and the attached JD with your
>> students and ask them to submit their formal application for the Software
>> Engineer Program on our Careers page at the earliest*.*
>>
>>
>>
>> *Please Note: The Code For Good event is the only way this year by which
>> the students can apply for the Software Engineer Program (SEP) at JP Morgan
>> Chase & Co. Hence, I request you to urge all eligible students to register
>> themselves for the Code For Good 2022 at the earliest.*
>>
>>
>>
>> *Eligibility Criteria for registration for the Software Engineer Program:*
>>
>>    - *Degrees:* B.Tech./B.E./MCA
>>    - 2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
>>    - 2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
>>    - *Streams or Specializations:* Computer Science/Information Science/
>>    Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
>>    Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
>>    - A well-rounded academic background with *minimum aggregate 7 CGPA
>>    [until date] in engineering course*
>>
>>
>>
>> *Registration Links:*
>>
>>    - The students from the 2023 graduating batch, who are applying for
>>    the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, should click here
>>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210245503/?utm_medium=jobshare> to
>>    register themselves.
>>    - The students from the 2024 graduating batch, who are applying for
>>    the Internship opportunity in 2023, should click here
>>    <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210247021/?utm_medium=jobshare> to
>>    register themselves.
>>
>>
>>
>> *Registration Dates:*
>>
>>    - The last day for registration for students from the 2024 graduating
>>    batch, who are applying for the Internship opportunity in 2023, is 16
>>    th March 2022.
>>    - The last day for registration for students from the 2023 graduating
>>    batch, who are applying for the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, is 16
>>    th March 2022.
>>
>>
>>
>> *Selection Process:*
>>
>>    - Eligible students register themselves on the JP Morgan Chase
>>    Careers page as per the given deadlines [as mentioned above].
>>    - All eligible students appear for an online coding test. We will
>>    share further details on the online tests at a later stage.
>>    - All eligible students appear for a video interview
>>    - JP Morgan Chase announces the final participant shortlist for the
>>    Code For Good events
>>
>>
>>
>> *Important Points to Know:*
>>
>>    1. Click ‘Apply Now’ and sign in with your JPMC career site username
>>    and associated personal email address. In case of you have previously
>>    signed up with your college email address, please edit the email address to
>>    your personal one before proceeding with this application. If you do not
>>    recall your password click forgot your password and follow the instructions
>>    2. Complete your application. If you are currently using an ‘.edu’
>>    email address please update it to a personal non ‘.edu’ email address.
>>    Failure to do so could cause delays in you receiving updates regarding your
>>    candidacy. You will be required to attach your resume with a Photograph on
>>    the right-hand/left-hand corner [Mandatory], kindly update your prior
>>    internship experience with other skills [optional].
>>    3. In case your campus does not appear in the application form,
>>    please select ‘other’ and mention the campus in the free text field.
>>    4. Click “Submit” to officially submit your application – a
>>    confirmation will be sent to the email address on your account when your
>>    application has been received
>>
>>
>>
>

snippet: Dear author, The peer review process of the paper has completed. We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees
subject:
FINAL REMINDER4 - Invitation for registration and presentation in AOTA -
  2023 (Deadline - 14th January)
body:
Dear author,

The peer review process of the paper has completed. We are happy to inform you that your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 14th January, 2023.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. RELATED INFORMATION AND COMMENTS IF APPLICABLE WILL BE SENT AFTER THE CONFERENCE. THERE WILL BE NO EXTRA CHARGES FOR THIS.

snippet: Folks, don't you agree we love fierce battles and clashes? There have been times when we admire villains more than heroes. Bolster up to see the rogues of Indian Cinema clashing against each other
subject: Vaatchal's Vishwakarndak'22 Edition out now!! Happy Reading!
body:
Folks, don’t you agree we love fierce battles and clashes?

There have been times when we admire villains more than heroes.

Bolster up to see the rogues of Indian Cinema clashing against each other
as we speak about the Vishwakarandak’22 - “The Scoundrels of Sin-ema!”

With us, endure the skirmishes of the departments of VIT, Pune as students
against each other hurdle up to the winner’s spot to shine in glory.

These battles aka different events are filled with none less than huge
gushes of adrenaline and clamour.

Vaatchal, this time, is here with the Vishwakrandak’22 edition to give you
these flickers of adrenaline.

Let the sins rise and shine!



Grab a copy of the Vishwakarandak’22 Edition right now and spread the word!

And as always, Happy reading!

Follow our Instagram page for more updates!

Regards,

Team Vaatchal.

*The 6th annual conference of Women Who Code Connect India 2022* is on 9th

snippet: Dear Student, If you are interested in NTU India Connect Summer Internship then please fill out this form https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc7aKMlI03ezHMYMw5ipLSEU2nkzRRNsoBVkq54_rfoSWYTwQ/
subject: NTU India Connect Summer Internship
body:
Dear Student,

  If you are interested in NTU India Connect Summer Internship then please
fill out this form

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc7aKMlI03ezHMYMw5ipLSEU2nkzRRNsoBVkq54_rfoSWYTwQ/viewform?usp=sf_link



 Please see the details on the website
https://www.ntu.edu.sg/about-us/global/india-connect-ntu/programme-details

The summer internship period is 10 May 2023 – 23 July 2023   and
application deadline to NTU Singapore  31st Jan 2023.

Nomination letter from VIT is mandatory for this Internship.

Eligibility: Student must have competed 5 semesters of UG study.
*Please note that cost of study travel stay and food will be bourn by
student only. Cost will be 4 to 6 Lakh Rs for the internship.*

The process of applications is as follows
1. All interested students must fill out this Google form  by  23 th Jan
2023.
2. After that interviews will be held for interaction with the student.
3. Final list of nominated students will be made by 27th Jan.
4. The finalized students must apply on NTU Singapore website by 31Jan 2023
and submit all necessary documents.

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: India Campus SEP Recruitment <
Date: Fri, Aug 19, 2022 at 8:28 PM
Subject: IMPORTANT | JPMorgan Chase & Co. | SEP Summer Internship 2023 |
Code for Good Selects - Vishwakarma Institute of Technology
To: tpo@vit.edu <tpo@vit.edu>
Cc: Nandan Wahi, Priyanka <

Hi Team,



We would like to thank you for your continued support to JP Morgan Chase &
Co.



As you may know, the selection process is extremely competitive. We were
fortunate to evaluate a talented pool of candidate(s) this year and the
below students truly stood out as exceptional. We were very impressed by
their talent, performance and qualifications. Based on their performance
during their interview, I am delighted to let you know that the below
mentioned candidate(s) will receive a written offer to join the firm
in *Software
Engineer Program* as a *Summer Intern 2023*.



In this position, they will have the opportunity to work with a talented,
collaborative team that is committed to doing the best for their clients.
They will be joining a firm that is committed to the continued growth of
its employees through robust training and development programs. We look
forward to their continued leadership and drive if they successfully
complete the preemployment screening and decide to join the Firm.



*First Name*

*Last Name*

*Candidate Email Address*

*College*

Tanishq

Deshpande

tanishq252002@gmail.com

Vishwakarma Institute of Technology

Arjun

Thakur

tarjun054@gmail.com

Vishwakarma Institute of Technology

Yash

yashgaherwar2002@gmail.com

Vishwakarma Institute of Technology

Soumil

Paranjpay

soumil.paranjpay20@vit.edu

Vishwakarma Institute of Technology

Harshit

harshitmundhra2@gmail.com

Vishwakarma Institute of Technology



Additionally, we would like to cover some important information about this
role:



*Tentative joining month*

April/May 2023

*Stipend*

INR 70,000 per month

*One Time Relocation Allowance*

INR 50,000



*Kindly confirm students’ acceptance on selection by* *10 AM on 23rd
August, 2022**. Also confirm the institute’s placement policy on selected
candidates, clarifying their further status with other companies scheduled
to hire for 2023 campus recruitment* *season.*



*As for next steps:*

   - The candidates, who decide to join the firm, will receive an email
   with a request to provide additional information, including their date of
   birth and national identifier. This information is required prior to
   generating their offer, so please ensure that they complete this form as
   soon as possible to avoid any delays.
   - They will receive the formal, written offer letter via email within 60
   days prior to their date of joining, which will provide additional details.
   - Before they get started in their new role, there are some
   pre-employment requirements that they must complete. This offer is
   contingent upon them successfully passing all pre-employment screening.
   They will receive instructions within approximately 60 days of their start
   date on how to access their electronic onboarding forms and be provided
   with additional details of other actions they will need to take. This offer
   is also contingent upon them being able to perform this role from their
   offer location, moving there if necessary, by their expected start date.
   - Once they successfully clear our pre-employment requirements, they
   will receive an official clearance notification email.



In the meantime, please feel free to reach out to me. We’re happy to answer
any questions you may have. We look forward to hearing back from you.



Thanks & Regards

snippet: Machine Learning For Options Trading Registration Link: shorturl.at/BDFZ6 Thursday, January 19, 2023 7:00 PM IST | About Session This session explains the application of machine learning techniques for
subject: Webinar on Machine Learning For Options Trading
body:
Machine Learning For Options Trading*Registration Link:  shorturl.at/BDFZ6
<http://shorturl.at/BDFZ6>*
Thursday, January 19, 2023
7:00 PM IST |
About Session

This session explains the application of machine learning techniques for
options trading. It also covers the process of creating options trading
strategies using machine learning.
Session Outline


   - Need for ML in options trading
   - ML for options pricing
   - Trading vertical spreads with ML
   - Options Trading with Ensemble Classifier
   - Forecasting and trading Implied Volatility with ML Regressor
   - Predicting The Returns of an Options Strategy using ML
   - Predicting The Options Strategy to Deploy using ML
   - Interactive Q&A

Pre-Requisites


   - Basic options nomenclature
   - Basic options trading strategies
   - Machine learning models





*Thank You and Regards,*
*Prof. Pankaj Kunekar*
*Assistant Professor*

*Department of IT*
*Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Pune*

snippet: TRF-2021-Elex-FY (Aditya Rotithor - aditya.rotithor19@vit.edu) Carefully read the instructions before starting the exam: 1. Questions are asked based on syllabus provided to you on WhatsApp groups. 2.
subject: TRF-2021-Elex-FY
body:
TRF-2021-Elex-FY


(Aditya Rotithor - aditya.rotithor19@vit.edu)
Carefully read the instructions before starting the exam:
1. Questions are asked based on syllabus provided to you on WhatsApp groups.
2. There are total 20 questions in this test.
3. Marks for particular question are shown on the top right corner of the
question block. The entire test comprises of 30 marks.
4. The test will automatically end after 45 minutes. Try to submit it before it
ends automatically to avoid any technical issues. (Timer will be shown at the
top)
5. There is no negative marking.

Important Note:
1. The recruitment team will be present in a meet throughout the exam duration.
So, if you have any technical issue while attempting your test, you can join the
meet to resolve it. (Link is provided on the WhatsApp group)
2. This test is an eliminating round. So, make sure you give the exam wisely.
3. Make sure that you are giving this test from your Desktop/laptop.
4. The plugin will ask access to share your entire screen. Please provide with
the same.
5. Please make sure you submit the test before the time ends. Or your response
wont be recorded.

All The Best !! 

Open the form https://quilgo.com/link/7Lk7DvLnIedktBPq 

Powered by Quilgo https://quilgo.com

(If using mobile, download future skills PRIME app
first)


2) On next screen you will see
https://learn.futureskillsprime.in/log_in?utm_source=futureskillsprime.in&utm_medium=Website&utm_campaign=FSPWebsite
website coming up, click on *Log in using credential*

3) Insert your email id and password as Welcome@123 (W is capital) , Click *log
in *and complete registration process that follows. Check if your *name is
entered correctly*, if not, edit and put correct name and follow the
process that follows.  This will help you to complete the registration

4) Once registration is completed click on *Groups* icon which is at top
left corner.

5) In groups you will see *Directorate of Technical Education* Group of
region – click on it

6) You can see courses their 1)  Fundamentals of Data Analytics Course by
Analyttica Treasure Hunt & SSC NASSCOM Assessment  2) Machine Learning -
Linear Regression Course by Analyttica Treasure Hunt & SSC NASSCOM
Assessment and 3) data science for beginners

7) Click on the course name  and register for the same.

Happy learning.

snippet: Dear all, Hope you're doing well Inviting your Incubator for the "Re-Imagining Markets Datathon" presented by NPCI, FCC & PCI in collaboration with SEBI, powered by Hack2skill.
subject:
Fwd: Invitation for DATAthon by NPCI & FCC in collaboration with SEBI
 (Govt. of India)
body:
Dear all,
[image: image.gif]

Hope you're doing well


Inviting your Incubator for the "*Re-Imagining Markets Datathon"* presented *by
NPCI, FCC & PCI* in collaboration *with SEBI*, powered by Hack2skill.


Opportunity to work with SEBI and be a part of its Advisory Committee.


It is a Virtual Datathon being organised as a part of the *Global Fintech
Fest*, which focuses on finding insights into Market-related data through
innovative analysis using modern technologies such as artificial
intelligence, machine learning and big data visualisation.


*Registration Open!*

Registrations closing: 11th September'22

Submission closing: 13th September'22

Checkout the details: LINK
<https://hack2skill-dot-yamm-track.appspot.com/2HQjNLV4F6tEXjLC5vd7f9lyPyK87BRF-fBaNc8aKLmWYGxsYgwHMHtU326HLA03YM_SpFDOHrEY4mHfl_FLhdtWpcQwbUaCQLK5IajVWdzzEzxoEcx7lOHzZp5n1F4MXUnOPz1toLCPOqrmRlMaQ-6GBm3WEg2Na867JCXP6Vkql_zjrikDPZeKjLwpXDPf_d5Rnpa6EynIwZkUTlRMG6nnoJvCo>


APOLOGIES FOR THE SHORT NOTICE

Since Time is of essence & the deadline is crisp.

The *Hackathon is LIVE as we speak*, I insist you to *extend this
Invitation to your Startup Network and students today itself*, so they can
start working towards their Ideations & Pitches for SEBI.


Contrary to a Typical Hackathon, This Datathon will happen in 2 Steps -

           Step 1: Idea Submission

           Step 2: Shortlisted Teams will Pitch their ideations to* SEBI
Jury.*
[image: main poster sebi.jpg]


The Datathon aims at providing a solution for the following finance-related
issues:

   - Visualisation of Performance
   - Forecasting trends


Winners will be getting a* chance to work with SEBI *and its advisory
committee, and will also receive Cash Prizes worth up to Rs 1.75 Lakhs


*Please add your Logo(s)* to the bottom right as shown in the sample
and *circulate
the same* amongst your start-up networks and students.

Thanks & Regards,
