snippet: Dear Academician / Researchers / Scholars / Students, MBien Analytica and Systems in association with Adonic Informatics is organizing 2 Days Hands-on Research Workshop on "BIBLIOMETRIC ANALYSIS
subject:
2 Days Hands-on Research Workshop on "BIBLIOMETRIC ANALYSIS USING R
 STUDIO and VOSviewer" on February 11th - 12th, 2023 through online mode
 (Google Meet)
body:
Dear Academician / Researchers / Scholars / Students,

MBien Analytica and Systems in association with Adonic Informatics is
organizing *2 Days Hands-on Research Workshop* on *"BIBLIOMETRIC ANALYSIS
USING R STUDIO and VOSviewer" *on *February 11th - 12th, 2023* through
online mode (Google Meet).

Date: February 11th - 12th, 2023 through online mode (Google Meet).

Interested researchers, students, academicians and faculty members of any
discipline / department can register for this workshop using the following
link:

Registration link:
*https://forms.gle/DV8L1E8okQVydHc87 <https://forms.gle/DV8L1E8okQVydHc87>*

Special features:

1. a) Software installation guide.

b) Live demonstrations of using R Studio and VOSviewer software for
bibliometric analysis.

2. Data acquisition

3. Bibliographic coupling

4. Citation analysis

5. Authorship relations

5. Bibliometric networks

6. Keyword analysis

7. Theme and trend analysis

8.  Most relevant journal analysis

9. Most relevant country analysis

10. Most relevant university analysis

AND MANY MORE.

*NOTE: E-certificates to all registered participants.*

*Registration fees can be paid through bank transfer /   UPI transfer.*

*PFA the flyer of the workshop.*

With best regards


Prof. S.P.Mondal

Adonic Informatics

Contact number : +91-9547361125 (Whats App)

Kolkata- 700154, West Bengal, India

subject: Call for Papers: TEMSMET 2023 (Third Edition)
body:
Dear All
go through trailing mail of Scopus IEEE Conference


*Thank You and Regards,*
*Prof. Pankaj Kunekar*
*Assistant Professor*

*Department of IT*
*Department of AI & DS*
*Vishwakarma Institute of Technology, Pune*
*Contact: 8237626369, 9075879342*





---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Pankaj Kunekar <pankajkunekar30@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, Nov 25, 2022 at 11:15 AM
Subject: Fwd: Reminder: Call for Papers: TEMSMET 2023 (Third Edition)
To: <pankaj.kunekar@vit.edu>




---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: IEEE eNotice <enotice@enotice.ieee.org>
Date: Fri, 25 Nov 2022 at 06:50
Subject: Reminder: Call for Papers: TEMSMET 2023 (Third Edition)
To: <pankajkunekar30@gmail.com>


If you are having trouble reading this message, click here
<https://enotice.mmsend.com/link.cfm?r=DD8-ZcJmY9B2uEZlBtVU-Q~~&pe=CPAk4zc_C3IboaPpCvCZdSAj_QwBwJeo7non6GtYGX4XoJKoIV0a7K2FcRGvmtJAYQG8noFa2Ma8o1ONup9c4Q~~&t=PatlEtNejMROH6AsGU3uDQ~~>
for the web version.

*IEEE THIRD INTERNATIONAL CONFERENCE ON TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING, MANAGEMENT
FOR SOCIETAL IMPACT USING MARKETING, ENTREPRENEURSHIP AND TALENT*

*IEEE TEMSMET 2023*

*February 10-11, 2023 | IEEE TEMS | VVIET, Mysuru, Karnataka, India  *

*CALL FOR PAPERS  *

*Final Paper Submission Deadline: November 20, 2022*

Dear Member,
IEEE Technology and Engineering Management Society, IEEE TEMS is organizing
the third edition of the International Conference IEEE TEMSMET 2023 -
TECHNOLOGY, ENGINEERING, MANAGEMENT FOR SOCIETAL IMPACT USING MARKETING,
ENTREPRENEURSHIP AND TALENT.  The Conference is hosted at VVIET, Mysuru, on
the 10th & 11th of February 2023.

The IEEE conference record #56707.

This conference provides an opportunity for academicians, researchers both
from technology and management backgrounds, students, industry experts,
analysts, business managers, and practitioners to present original research
and innovative solutions on the latest innovations and research
advancements in the areas of next-generation electronics, technology,
engineering, management, entrepreneurship, and innovation to help
technology management.

We, on behalf of the organizing team of TEMSMET 2023, invite you to submit
Full-length original research contributions and review articles at TEMSMET
2023

*Early bird Submission Deadline:  25 November 2022*

*Full Paper Submission Deadline:  10 December 2022*

*Notification of Acceptance: 20 December 2022*

*Last Date for Registration: 12 January 2023*

*Submit a Paper:* https://cmt3.research.microsoft.com/TEMSMET2023
<https://enotice.mmsend.com/link.cfm?r=DD8-ZcJmY9B2uEZlBtVU-Q~~&pe=eLO5wtyVh99OuOxb7xjPn6Q_uw6hfy-HjUw0NE5RpEHvTV-ZrqERCjXmFdFzrmqWW1spfLog8-MOPLYGqzuiJA~~&t=PatlEtNejMROH6AsGU3uDQ~~>

*Conference Webpage:* https://temsmetvviet.com/
<https://enotice.mmsend.com/link.cfm?r=DD8-ZcJmY9B2uEZlBtVU-Q~~&pe=5lDPy6puIuL77VUcVxnAp-nVGk1PvmRpgFRJfD6ufTSyFk7BNPjKr0c2nqpc7IxJnrQiN9T2G0Kk4kaJKjFWpg~~&t=PatlEtNejMROH6AsGU3uDQ~~>


We request you to encourage your peers, friends, researchers,  industry
experts, analysts, business managers, and practitioners in your network to
submit their quality submissions to IEEE TEMSMET-2023. We look forward to
your participation and support.

In case of any clarifications, please send an email to:
temsmet2023@gmail.com


With Warm Regards,
On behalf of the TEMSMET-2023 Organizing Committee,

Dr. Bindu A. Thomas,
General Chair TEMSMET2023,
Vice Chair 2022, IEEE Education Society
Founder Chair, IEEE Mysore Subsection,
Professor & Head, Dept. of ECE, VVIET, Mysuru.

Dr. Shrikant Tangade,
General Chair TEMSMET2023,
Secretary-2022, IEEE TEMS Conferences & Events Committee,
Assoc. Prof, CSE Dept., CHRIST (Deemed To Be University), Bangalore, India.

snippet: Flipkart GRiD 4.0 - Software Development Challenge Flipkart Hi Om surushe, We've always worked on creating engagements that give you a platform to explore your skills and go beyond defined horizons
subject: Flipkart GRiD is in the race for Unstop Awards 2023 | Vote Now!
body:
Flipkart GRiD 4.0 - Software Development Challenge

Flipkart

Hi Om surushe,

We’ve always worked on creating engagements that give you a platform to explore your skills and go beyond defined horizons to showcase your talent. We hope you had a good experience while being a part of Flipkart GRiD 4.0. Your support really helped us create an impact. 

Today, we need your support again! Unstop Awards 2023 has been launched & you’ve got the opportunity to make your move and vote for Flipkart GRiD 4.0 under Unstop Prestigious B-School Campus Engagements 2023.

Vote Now

Your vote matters to recognize the competitions that gave you new learnings & the motivation to keep doing well.

We look forward to being a part of your top favourite campus engagements and hope for the best ones to win!

Regards,
Flipkart Team

Disclaimer: This email has been sent to you on behalf of Flipkart, organizer of Flipkart GRiD 4.0 - Software Development Challenge

Follow us for informative & cute content:

Unstop Coin Store

Proud parent of our app:

on the opportunity page or to us at support@unstop.com

snippet: Dear author, Your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023. A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION
subject:
FINAL REMINDER5 - Invitation for registration and presentation in AOTA -
  2023 (Deadline - 14th January)
body:
Dear author,

Your paper has been recommended for PRESENTATION ONLY in AOTA-2023.


A special reduced registration fees of Rs 2000 per paper is applicable for ONLY PRESENTATION & NO PUBLICATION assigned papers. Presentation certificate will be provided to the authors.


You are invited for registration for presenting your paper in AOTA.


After paying the registration fees, the corresponding / submitting author must fill the registration form as given below.


https://forms.gle/wXpFB897SNxD8iux6


Registration deadline: 14th January, 2023.


With best regards


TEAM AOTA

NOTE: THERE IS NO NEED TO UPLOAD REVISED PAPER NOW. YOUR PAPER MAY BE CONSIDERED FOR PUBLICATION AS CHAPTERS IN EDITED BOOKS OF HIGHLY REPUTED INTERNATIONAL PUBLISHERS AFTER THE CONFERENCE SUBJECTED TO FURTHER IMPROVEMENTS AND REVISIONS IN THE PAPER. Congratulations on joining AWS Educate, your place to skill up on all things cloud

So what’s next? If you’re brand new to the cloud, we recommend starting with our Introduction to Cloud 101 course. It will help you learn and practice AWS Cloud fundamentals through hands-on labs.

Ready to accelerate your cloud journey? Then the Getting Started series is for you. These courses are designed to help you learn how to build with foundational AWS services in storage, networking and compute.

Once you’ve completed Introduction to Cloud 101 or any of the courses in the Getting Started series, you’ll earn a digital badge which will give you access to our exclusive AWS Emerging Talent Community, where you can network with early career talent just like you. snippet: Call for Code Fair Work Case Competition Uniting students to design solutions for a sustainable and equitable global economic future. How can technology address the challenge of making decent job
subject: Call for Code Fair Work Case Competition
body:
IBM Academic Initiative

Call for Code Fair Work Case Competition
 Uniting students to design solutions for a sustainable and equitable global economic future.

How can technology address the challenge of making decent job creation, entrepreneurship, and fair, sustainable labor a lifelong opportunity of economic growth for all?

On October 6, Call for Code, presented by IBM and the Clinton Global Initiative University, will launch the 2022 Call for Code Fair Work Case Competition. The competition calls on collegiate-level students around the world to imagine innovative solutions that advances the future of work.

The challenge will run October 6-20, 2022 and asks both non-technical and technical university-level student teams to devise innovative business cases that can advance inclusive, scalable workforce development. The competition theme is inspired by the United Nations Sustainable Development Goal 8 https://sdgs.un.org/goals/goal8. Solutions should address one of the diverse challenges aligned to this theme and demonstrate how technology can help communities in need. While solution submissions do not need to include working code, teams will need to describe the technologies required and how those technologies fit into the solution. 

Answer the call

As current students, the world needs your expertise, empathy, and unique perspective. Get mentored by entrepreneurs, technologists, and leaders during the competition. Network with other university students from around the world, and compete for prizes from a total pool of $22,000 USD, which includes a $12,000 USD grand prize!

Register for the Case Competition today and help design the fair work of the future.
Learn more and get started

Answer the call https://callforcode-case.bemyapp.com/?utm_source=cfc&utm_medium=student
									 https://callforcode-case.bemyapp.com/?utm_source=cfc&utm_medium=student

snippet: Dear JP Morgan Registered, Please go through below mail received from the company and do the needful. All the best! Thanks. AS Mitragotri TPO, VIT ---------- Forwarded message --------- Date: Wed, Mar
subject:
Fwd: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Registration Process open
 for 2022 Software Engineer Program
body:
Dear J P Morgan Registered,

Please go through below mail received from the company and *do the needful*.

All the best!
Thanks.
A.S. Mitragotri
TPO,
VIT



---------- Forwarded message ---------

Date: Wed, Mar 9, 2022 at 2:37 PM
Subject: IMPORTANT | JP Morgan Chase & Co. | Registration Process open for
2022 Software Engineer Program



The registration process for the Code For Good 2022 is now open!



*Please share the below registration details and the attached JD with your
students and ask them to submit their formal application for the Software
Engineer Program on our Careers page at the earliest. *



*Please Note: The Code For Good event is the only way this year by which
the students can apply for the Software Engineer Program (SEP) at JP Morgan
Chase & Co. Hence, I request you to urge all eligible students to register
themselves for the Code For Good 2022 at the earliest. *



*Eligibility Criteria for registration for the Software Engineer Program:*

   - *Degrees:* B.Tech./B.E./MCA
   - 2023 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Full-Time opportunity]
   - 2024 Batch Pass-outs [eligible for Internship opportunity]
   - *Streams or Specializations:* Computer Science/Information Science/
   Information Technology/Data Science/Artificial Intelligence/Big
   Data/IoT/Electronics/ Electrical/Electronics and Telecommunications etc.
   - A well-rounded academic background with *minimum aggregate 7 CGPA
   [until date] in engineering course*



*Registration Links:*

   - The students from the 2023 graduating batch, who are applying for the
   Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, should click here
   <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210245503/?utm_medium=jobshare>
   to register themselves.
   - The students from the 2024 graduating batch, who are applying for the
   Internship opportunity in 2023, should click here
   <https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/job/210247021/?utm_medium=jobshare>
   to register themselves.



*Registration Dates:*

   - *The last day for registration for students from the 2024 graduating
   batch, who are applying for the Internship opportunity in 2023, is 16th
   March 2022. *
   - *The last day for registration for students from the 2023 graduating
   batch, who are applying for the Full-Time Analyst opportunity in 2023, is
   16th March 2022. *



*Selection Process:*

   - Eligible students register themselves on the JP Morgan Chase Careers
   page as per the given deadlines [as mentioned above].
   - All eligible students appear for an online coding test. We will share
   further details on the online tests at a later stage.
   - All eligible students appear for a video interview
   - JP Morgan Chase announces the final participant shortlist for the Code
   For Good events



*Important Points to Know:*

   1. Click ‘Apply Now’ and sign in with your JPMC career site username and
   associated personal email address. In case of you have previously signed up
   with your college email address, please edit the email address to your
   personal one before proceeding with this application. If you do not recall
   your password click forgot your password and follow the instructions
   2. Complete your application. If you are currently using an ‘.edu’ email
   address please update it to a personal non ‘.edu’ email address. Failure to
   do so could cause delays in you receiving updates regarding your candidacy.
   You will be required to attach your resume with a Photograph on the
   right-hand/left-hand corner [Mandatory], kindly update your prior
   internship experience with other skills [optional].
   3. In case your campus does not appear in the application form, please
   select ‘other’ and mention the campus in the free text field.
   4. Click “Submit” to officially submit your application – a confirmation
   will be sent to the email address on your account when your application has
   been received


<jaishree.bagul@jpmchase.com>



Thanks & Regards

*Karthik Sai K* | Human Resources | *J.P. Morgan* |




This message is confidential and subject to terms at:
https://www.jpmorgan.com/emaildisclaimer including on confidential,
privileged or legal entity information, malicious content and monitoring of
electronic messages. If you are not the intended recipient, please delete
this message and notify the sender immediately. Any unauthorized use is
strictly prohibited.

Dear Sir/Ma'am,

Hope all is well :)

In reference to our conversation on WhatsApp, I am sharing the details
about our organisation along with the openings available.
I am sorry for the delayed response but we were waiting for a few roles to
open up.

*About The Apprentice Project-TAP*

TAP is a not for profit organization committed to supporting children from
low-income communities to explore who they are and achieve what they want
to do. TAP uses choice-based
learning (Visual arts, Performance arts or STEM) and socio-emotional skills
as methods to develop children into future leaders. We do this with our *online
WhatsApp-based platform* with volunteer mentor support and *Classroom based
model* to ensure all children can express how they feel and learn what they
love from home.
The TAP leadership team comprises* alumni *from the* Indian Institute of
Management, Teach For India, and Harvard University.*

In *2020-21* TAP supported 2000+ children directly with *60% of them
shwoing an increase in skill *and extended the curriculum/content further
to various organizations supporting *10,000+ children. *

body:
Yes! the Biggest Annual Hackathon is Here! 😁
[image: sc-01.png]

Greetings from GDSC VIT Pune! ✨

<https://gdsc.community.dev/events/details/developer-student-clubs-gdsc-global-presents-gdsc-solution-challenge-2023-kickoff>
🤩
which is an annual global contest organized by Google in which developers
are invited to use their ways to find innovative solutions to real-world
problems 🧑‍💻.

The mission of the 2023 Solution Challenge is to solve one or more of
the United
Nations' 17 Sustainable Development Goals 🎯.

By participating in this hackathon, you will have the opportunity to make a
positive impact on the world and be rewarded for your hard work and
creativity 🏆. Your ideas and innovations will be eligible for an
impressive range of prizes, and you also have a chance to receive
mentorship from Google experts.

The tentative timeline ⌛ for the hackathon is of *two months*, starting
from Jan 18th to Mar 30th, 2023.

We look forward to seeing you there and working together to find innovative
solutions to some of the world's most pressing problems. ⚡

*Further details will be provided to you at the info session (online) on:*

a difference!*

snippet: Dear Student, End semester examinations for BTech First Year are from 4th to 7th May 2021. MCQ-End semester examination subject wise schedule is attached herewith. Following are the instructions for
subject: FY B.Tech ESE MCQ schedule, Dummy Exam schedule and instructions
body:
Dear Student,

End semester examinations for BTech First Year are from 4th to 7th May
2021.

MCQ-End semester examination subject wise schedule is attached herewith.

Following are the instructions for MCQ-ESE:
1. Login using VIERP.
2. Students must ensure the charging of laptops. (In case of electricity
failure at student end).
3. Students must ensure availability of internet enabled Laptop. It is
compulsory to give an exam using a laptop computer, no other device is
permitted.
4. Students must keep video on during exams. If the video is off, the exam
will be paused by proctor.
5. It is compulsory for students to join google meet/Zoom meeting, link
will be shared by individual subject teacher (proctor)
6. For subjects ES1031: Cognitive Aptitude / ES1032: Engineering
Mathematics, every student will get 60 questions per subject. Duration for
this is 2 hours. For all other subjects every student will get 40 questions
per subject, duration for the exam will be 1 hour and  30 mins.

7. Also you will get 15 mins more to each subject. These first 15 mins in
each subject’s exam, are to join google meet and to give attendance.

8. Every student will get randomly selected questions from the subject's
question bank; answer options will be shuffled for each student.

9. In case of any malpractice, students will get punishment as per
Institute policy.

Following are the instructions for Dummy exam



1. For each subject a dummy exam will be conducted, a time table of the
dummy exam is attached.

2. It is compulsory to give a dummy exam.



In case of any query, do not reply to this mail, you can ask your queries
to subject teachers. In case of any issue during the exam, contact the
subject teacher only.



Exams will be conducted, monitored and proctored by subject teachers only.


*******Do not reply to this email. *******


Dean Examinations
Vishwakarma Institute of technology, Pune

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Intel Training <intel.openvino.toolkit@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, Oct 11, 2022 at 11:48 AM
Subject: Intel's AI for Youth - October 14, 2022
To: Intel Training <intel.openvino.toolkit@gmail.com>























Intel Technologies takes immense pleasure in welcoming the 1st Year & 2nd
Year CS/IT/ECE/IS students of your institute to be a part of the Intel "AI
for Youth" Bootcamp starting this Oct 14th, 2022.


Why AI for Youth?

Today’s students are tomorrow’s innovators. While the impact of Emerging
Technologies like AI is undeniable, the degree to which it influences and
prepares youth is immeasurable. Thus, even though AI is everywhere, the
opportunity to benefit from it and shape it is not.

The next generation of innovators needs the right skills and resources to
understand what AI is, how it is designed, and
why it is important in today’s digital world. Otherwise, the digital skills
gap will only increase and further hurt economies
and society. Moreover, many young people don’t yet fully grasp the key role
they can play in shaping AI.

Hence, it is essential to demystify and democratize AI for the next
generation of innovators in an inclusive way,
irrespective of gender, ethnicity or location.

Providing them the opportunity to learn AI skills and apply them
responsibly to design any solution is an important key
to building long-term competitiveness.


Program Goals

   -

   Deep understanding of AI: Demystify AI and equip youth with the skill
   sets and mindsets required for AI readiness.
   -

   Access and use of AI toolsets: Democratize access to AI tools with Intel
   technologies and train youth to use them
   skillfully.
   -

   Create solutions with AI: Meaningful social impact solutions as evidence
   of achievement.



Program Approach

   -

    Pricing: FREE of Cost
   -

    Mode of Training: Online
   -

   Covering three AI Domains: Computer Vision, Natural Language Processing
   and Statistical Data.
   -

   Date and Time: Begins from Oct 14, 2022.  Time as per students'
   convenience.
   -

   Audience: *S*tudents from 1st Year and 2nd Year. (Ages from 13 through
   19).
   -

   *Minimum Participation *per college:- 100+ students
   -

   Prerequisite: No prior coding experience required; only foundational
   math and statistics skills.
   -

   Duration: 2 Hours, for 12 days
   -

   Certificate: Certificate of Participation for all and Certificate of
   Accomplishment offered to those
   youth building and showcasing AI-enabled projects to solve real-world
   problems.



*S. No.*

*DATE*

*TIME SLOTS AVAILABLE*

*LINK FOR REGISTRATION*

1





*Oct 14, 2022  - Oct 27, 2022*

5:00 PM to 7:00 PM



*https://bit.ly/Intel-AI4Youth-14-October-2022
<https://bit.ly/Intel-AI4Youth-14-October-2022> *

*Please copy & paste the registration link in the browser to register*

2

7:00 PM to 9:00 PM



Skills Gained

   -

   Technical skills: Programming and coding, data science, computer vision,
   natural language processing,
   statistical data and algorithmic and computational thinking.
   -

   Social skills: AI ethics and bias reduction, critical thinking,
   problem-solving, system mapping, AI solutions building,
   and social and emotional skills.




*Contact: -*

WhatsApp or Call @ +91 8217600313

Email:- bootcamp@aiforyouth.org

Website:- https://intel.ly/3BSKXBC

snippet: Dear all, Participate in Student Innovation Festival – IISF 2022 F.No. AICTE/P&AP/Misc/Jan/2023 Date: 09.01.2023 Circular To, All Vice Chancellors of Technical Universities and All Directors/
subject:
=?UTF-8?Q?Fwd=3A_Request_to_participate_in_Student_Innovation_Fe?=
	=?UTF-8?Q?stival_=E2=80=93_IISF_2022_=2D_reg=2E?=
body:
Dear all,

*Participate in Student Innovation Festival – IISF 2022*


*F.No. AICTE/P&AP/Misc/Jan/2023


                  Date: 09.01.2023*
*Circular*

* To,*


*All Vice Chancellors of Technical Universities and **        All
Directors/Principals of AICTE Approved Institutions.*

            *India International Science Festival (IISF) *is a platform for
public participation to inculcate scientific perspective and promote
interest in science. Seven editions of IISF have been organized at various
places across the country in the past. This year, eighth edition of IISF is
being organized at *Maulana Azad Naitonal Institute of Technology (MANIT),
Bhopal, Madhya Pradesh.* Theme for the 8th edition of IISF is Marching
Towards Amrit Kaal with Science, Technology and Innovation.

             *Students Innovation Festival (SIF)* is an event of IISF where
college level onwards students participate in competition and also showcase
their talents on an international stage. The Themes of SIF-2022 are:
*Developing
Sustainable Life based on Five Elements of Nature: The Earth, The Water,
The fire, The air and The space*. Students from engineering as well as
science streams, who are interested and involved in innovation and
creativity can participate in the *Students’ Innovation Festival
(SIF-2022).*

            The selected models/entries will be showcased in the IISF on *22-23
January, 2023 at MANIT, Bhopal*. Registration can be done on the website
https://scienceindiafest.org
<https://ind01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fscienceindiafest.org%2F&data=05%7C01%7CSubhash.Kumar%40lntinfotech.com%7Cdcc716fce2c24c4a93fd08daf23fd8d7%7C02aa9fc118bc4798a020e01c854dd434%7C1%7C0%7C638088653485414394%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=rRM%2FNkIuZQR7VkXtLUqf67YnjGxHH6UB5Xt%2FQEQgQro%3D&reserved=0>
. For detailed information, *Brochure and Poster of SIF-2022 are enclosed
herewith*. The last date for registration by the students is *13th January,
2023.*

            In this regard you are requested to encourage students at your
institutions to be part of such endeavour towards innovation. Your
cooperation will help the students of every corner of our country to have
opportunity to participate in such an event of National importance.

PFA:-
https://drive.google.com/file/d/130Ou99W9nwpPgauG-iX5B_3rWZ5shrtb/view?usp=share_link


PFA:-
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1i7_aoKukYzS9LjbT8W-mtGD7AYJ454qm/view?usp=share_link





*Regards, **(Dr. Ramesh Unnikrishnan)*


*                                      Advisor-II**Policy & Academic
Planning Bureau*


-- 
Best regards,


Prof(Dr.) Premanand P. Ghadekar
M.Tech, Ph. D, LMISTE
Professor & Head,
Department of Information Technology
Vishwakarma Institute of Technology Pune-37
Phone-020-24202177, 917276028816
email-hodit@vit.edu, premanand.ghadekar@vit.edu

snippet: Dear all, Lab exams for following courses are scheduled during 21st Nov to 6th Dec, pls refer to the schedule sent by Exam coordinator. In this regard please note the following important points: 1.
subject: REGARDING FINAL LAB EXAMS
body:
Dear all,
Lab exams for following courses are scheduled during 21st Nov to 6th Dec,
pls refer to the schedule sent by Exam coordinator.
In this regard please note the following important points:
1. Timing for the lab exam will be 9am to 6pm. Reporting time for the exam
is 8:30am. Total exam duration will be 2hrs
2. Exams will be conducted according to  ROLL NO wise.
3. Exams will be conducted for 100 marks: 50 marks for implementation with
correct output and 50 marks for overall assignment performance.
4. Random Chit system for selection of problem statement
5. In case of a change lab assignment statement 20 marks out of 100 will be
deducted.
6. Any other doubts will be solved by the respective subject teacher or lab
teacher.



Thanks and Regards
-----------------------------------------------------------
*Deepali Rahul Deshpande *
*PhD Research Scholar at Shivaji University,*
*Assistant Professor *
*Assistant Head, Academics *
*Department of Information Technology *
*Vishwakarma Institute of Technology,Bibwewadi,*
*Pune 411037,Maharashtra, India*
*Email ID: deepali.deshpande@vit.edu <deepali.deshpande@vit.edu>  *
*9665095574*

 =?utf-8?Q?=E2=80=93?= Experiential Project Based Learning Program.

project-based learning program a unique and first of its kind
initiative form Government of Tamil Nadu.

snippet: Dear Academician / Researchers / Scholars / Students, Adonic Informatics and MBien Analytica and Systems is organizing National Research Workshop on "Writing a Review Paper: Innovative ways of
subject:
National Research Workshop on "Writing a Review Paper: Innovative
 ways of using Tables, Flowcharts, and Graphs" on 23rd January, 2023
body:
Dear Academician / Researchers / Scholars / Students,

Adonic Informatics and MBien Analytica and Systems is organizing *National
Research Workshop* on *"Writing a Review Paper: Innovative ways of using
Tables, Flowcharts, and Graphs"* on *23rd January, 2023 through online mode
(Google Meet).*

*Workshop Date : 23/01/2023 (3 PM onwards)*

*Registration link:*
*https://forms.gle/Ej9gqgWxKXwyns337 <https://forms.gle/Ej9gqgWxKXwyns337>*

Faculty members, research scholars, researchers, PG and UG students of all
departments / disciplines.

The workshop will focus on how to write a structured review paper with
special focus on the uses of *SPECIALLY DESIGNED TABLES, FLOW CHARTS and
GRAPHS* for review papers.

*NOTE: E-certificates to all registered participants.*

*Registration fees can be paid through bank transfer /   UPI transfer.*

*PFA the flyer.*

With best regards


Prof. S.P.Mondal

Adonic Informatics

Contact number : +91-9547361125 (Whats App)

Kolkata- 700154, West Bengal, India

snippet: Come get your doubts resolved and get your career mentorship from industry professionals and from other students internationally! Join us on Discord! Please disregard this email if you have already
subject: Join Studustry's community on Discord for free!
body:
Come get your doubts resolved and get your career mentorship from industry professionals and from other students internationally! Join us on Discord!

Please disregard this email if you have already joined us on Discord!

Hello 

Thank you for showing interest in for *Studustry!*

*As a part of rewarding people who have supported us during our initial phases, we are opening up the Studustry community specially for you.*

The Studustry community has a special channel on Discord ( https://discord.com/ ) which has students from all sectors participating in discussions with themselves and industry professionals who are willing to mentor young students.

Ask questions about your resume, career paths, interesting research topics, projects, internships and overall professional development!

Studustry team will also be posting all the project opportunities on Discord first! *And the best part??*

I *t's absolutely free!*

As you all might already know, universities are now making project based learning a mandatory part of the curriculum and what better way to make yourself future-proof than joining a community about project based learning!

So, what are you waiting for! Click on the button below and join the Studustry community !

Join Studustry Discord Channel ( https://discord.gg/3HdxwDJ8 )

Studustry is a startup based in Pune & Aurangabad bringing the concept of project based learning to colleges in India. Look for our LinkedIn page to learn more about us.
Join the only project based learning community of India today by getting in touch with us.
Use this link if you would like to discuss anything in particular by directly chatting with us.

( https://www.facebook.com/studustry/ ) ( https://twitter.com/studustry?lang=en ) ( https://www.instagram.com/studustry/?hl=en ) ( https://www.linkedin.com/company/studustry/ )

snippet: Dear Students, We are excited to announce an upcoming event on investment opportunities for college students. The event will be held on Date : 21st Jan 2023 Time : 4 PM - 6 PM Venue : 1326 Speaker :
subject: An amazing session on Investing in Early 20's by The Investment Forum.
body:
Dear Students,

We are excited to announce an upcoming event on investment
opportunities for college students. The event will be held on
Date : 21st Jan 2023
Time : 4 PM - 6 PM
Venue : 1326
Speaker : Prof. Dr. Rajesh Dhake,
                Dean - Student Activities, VIT Pune.

During the event, we will be discussing various investment options,
such as stocks, bonds, and mutual funds, and how they can be used to
build a strong financial foundation for your future. We will also be
providing tips and strategies for successful investing, as well as
answering any questions you may have.

This event is open to all college students, regardless of their major
or prior knowledge of investing. We encourage all students to attend,
as the information and resources provided will be valuable in helping
you achieve your financial goals.

We look forward to seeing you there!

Regards,
Team TIF.

& Co.!

snippet: Dear Students, We are thrilled to announce that we are recruiting for the very first time. 📣 QUARK is a club that aims to Ideate, Collaborate and Innovate. We are looking for passionate and dedicated
subject: Team Quark - Recruitment Now Open!
body:
*Dear Students,*


We are thrilled to announce that we are recruiting for the very first time.
📣


*QUARK* is a club that aims to *Ideate, Collaborate and Innovate*. We are
looking for passionate and dedicated individuals who share our mission and
vision to join our team.


As a team member of QUARK, you will have the opportunity to:


📌 For FY students:

   -

   Operations
   -

   Creative Team



📌 For SY and TY students:

   -

   Technical Team
   -

   Creative Team


Here are some details about the recruitment drive :

We will be recruiting for both *technical* and *non-technical* domains.


The *Non-Technical* areas in which we will be recruiting are listed below.

   -

   Operations
   -

   Creative Team


The* Technical *areas in which we will be recruiting are listed below.

   -

   AI/ML
   -

   Competitive Programming
   -

   Cyber Security
   -

   ROS
   -

   Rust
   -

   App Development
   -

   Web Development
   -

   UI/UX


To apply, please click the button below.
Apply Now <https://www.teamquark.com/apply/>

*Visit our website to learn more about the recruitment drive. *
https://www.teamquark.com/recruitment/



We look forward to seeing you at our recruitment events and welcoming you
to our team.
